Title: 2003 Ford Ranger XLT 4dr SuperCab FX4 / 1-OWNER / 87K MILES / CLEAN 4dr SuperCab
2002 Audi A4 1.8T Quattro - Rare 5 Speed, K04 Turbo and MORE!!
Description:
It really, truly pains me to part with this beauty. :( 

Sorry for the 'novel' in advance.... \/


Due to another baby on the way, I simply needed to get a larger vehicle to fit two car seats comfortably.  I have driven this car over 30,000 miles and it has been outstandingly reliable, practical, fun, and safe.  It has ALWAYS been professionally maintained (see stack of service records for proof) by local fantastic German autoshop, J&J Werkstadt here in Albany, and has never been involved in an accident.

Now the fun stuff!! :D About a year and a half ago (rough estimate.. I lost the original invoice and am waiting for a copy to be emailed to me) I had big plans to turn this car into much more than a simple daily driver for a real estate agent.  I wanted something that was in 'sleeper' territory.  So, here's what I had Double J Motorwerks in Portland do for me:

-Install K04 Turbo with an upgraded big billet wheel
-Install bigger 550cc injectors
-Install tubular turbo manifold
-Cat delete, down pipe installed in its place
-Reconfigured intake solution 
-Custom tune built from the ground up specifically made for my car.  NOT a 'generic' APR tune!!

After everything was said and done, it completely transformed this car.  It has not been put on a dyno, but according to DJM they estimate with this configuration I am likely in the neighborhood of 240-260hp.  They said that the stock exhaust system is a bottleneck, and if I went to a 3" catback exhaust there would be a lot more headroom! 

Back in May of 2017, I had Les Shwab put a fresh set of Toyo Proxes 4+ tires put on and I'd guesstimate that there is still over 50% tread left on them.  Alignment is still dead center too, I had the tires rotated a few months ago, might be due for another rotation.  

I could literally go on and on about this car as I know it essentially inside and out, so if there are any specific questions/concerns you may have, feel free to reach out to me and I'd be happy to fill you in.  Like I said above about the BIG job from DJM, I will have a replacement copy of the original invoice from that work.  They always get back to me very quickly!  

Here's what I like and dislike about the car.  As much as I wish it were, this car isn't all daisies and butterflies, it's got a few dings here and there and some quirks but.. For being a 16 year old car, it's pretty damn immaculate and I've tried everything in my power (and wallet..) to keep her that way. :)


What I LOVE:

-Car is wicked fast.  Turbo spools up very quickly and will push you back into your seat.  Very little turbo lag :) 

-Interior is damn-near spotless.  Leather seats are in fantastic condition, front and back heated seats all work and are a BLESSING during winter!!

-5 SPEED!!  Finding a CLEAN A4 like mine in a 5 speed is pretty much a unicorn.  

-Sits pretty low stock actually.. I really wouldn't bother messing with the suspension, I think it's at a 'function-ably' friendly level of 'low'.

-Quattro. AWD BABY!!  This car just hugs the road on every corner, you'll never lose traction.  Even during the crazy snowstorm of 2016 (I think it was 2016..?) that buried Albany, I was still very easily able to get to and from the office in this car.  
-Probably a bunch of other stuff that I currently can't think of until I sit in the car again and get reminded. ;)

-Professionally installed single din Kenwood Bluetooth deck (I don't have the model number in front of me currently, but can give it to you on request) by the Stereo Store here in Albany.  It's got loads of settings, handsfree calling (necessity for a real estate agent..), aux, and dual USB ports.  

-On the subject of sound... This car's original Bose system is PHENOMENAL!!  I honestly have had no reason to upgrade it to anything else because it has held up so well!!  None of the speakers are blown or rattling. the dedicated subwoofer is respectable too..  Very impressive for a 16 year old car!!  

-Timing belt + water pump recently serviced.  I don't have the exact date/mileage, it's on one of the yellow invoices from J&J, but I'd estimate it was done about 10k-15k miles ago. 


What I'm Not a Fan of:
-Passenger side rear fender by wheel is dented and 'ripply' looking.  It has been like this since I bought the car and no idea what could have caused it as the paint isn't chipping or anything..  Just strange.  Not super noticeable, just bothers me on occasion when I do see it.  I have a friend that works at Main Auto Body in Salem that got me an estimate to fix it and it really wasn't worth it to me to have it done.  I can share the invoice with you if you do want it, it came to something like $1200.

-Damn check engine light is on because I wanted it to have a more free-flowing exhaust and remove the catalytic converter.  Every time I have my oil changed I have J&J Werkstadt run the codes though just to make sure there aren't any other faults.  So far it has only been the missing o2 sensor due to the down pipe.  If you're concerned, feel free to bring a scanner with you and check it yourself though.  

-On driver side passenger door near handle there is a bit of a nasty 'keyed' mark that has been there since I bought the car.  Luckily, clear coat has not started chipping due to it, which is quite surprising because it is a pretty visibly deep scratch.  Like the bent up fender above, this just has not been on the priority to-do list and wasn't worthwhile to me to have done. 

-The diverter valve may need to be replaced.  Occasionally I will randomly hear the signature 'turbo surge' sound and the last time this happened, it was because the stock DV was sticking.  Dirt cheap fix, you could even do it yourself pretty easily if you wanted. I just haven't had the time.

-Stock clutch.  It still shifts fantastic, but I am sure that this is going to be the next maintenance item as I have been driving this car with this clutch for the past 30,000+ miles.  Just something to keep an eye on.

-Fuel economy is pretty crappy for a 4cyl 5 speed..  Before the new sexy turbo and big injectors I was getting 28+mpg on the freeway but now that's optimistically averaged around 22mpg.  Expect a fuel tank to get you about 330 miles before you gotta fill up.  Oh yeah, and it HAS to be premium ONLY because of the tune.  DO NOT FILL IT WITH REGULAR EVER!!


Okay, that's all I've got for now.  Hit me up with questions.  SERIOUS BUYERS ONLY.  If you have a car to sell first, take care of that before inquiring.  I am not letting just anybody take this bad boy for a spin, you've gotta have financing in order or cash in hand.  Lowballs/trades not considered.  I already bought the replacement vehicle so this car is just sitting pretty until the right buyer comes along.  I have soooooo much money/emotional attachment to this car.

Text/email is quickest way to get ahold of me, but if you leave a voicemail I'll try to get back to you as soon as possible:

5four1-9sevenfour-19seven8

Title: 1975 Mercedes Benz 240D
Description:
This is a vintage/classic car, ready for you to convert to vegetable oil if you desire.  It is the W115 body, which makes it a rarity; I have only seen two others in town.  I am the third owner.  It spent the first 40 years of it's life in Southern California so there is no rust and the body is in excellent condition.  Unfortunately I moved back to Oregon and I don't have a place to park it indoors, and I feel like it is not getting the love and care it deserves sitting out under a cedar tree!  It is incredibly reliable, but it could use a tune up since it has been sittting around for so long (I fire it up every month or so, but it's not getting much use).  I was hoping it would be my son's some day, but I just need to face the fact that I don't have time/room for a car that isn't being driven every day!

The Good:
Body is in great shape!
Runs well, no mechanical/engine issues
Low miles: odometer says 65,000, previous owner claimed it was 150,000, so even if you add some extra and call it 265,000 the engine is only halfway through it's life.  This particular car is known as the "million mile engine," google it
30 MPG, not bad for a 40-year-old car
Easy to work on--that's part of the reason I bought it, I like to do my own work when I can.  Therefore...
Comes with specialized tools.  I have a set of custom wrenches, so you can do the valves and change the oil etc.  Plus 2 manuals and a box or two of assorted parts for maintenance
I replaced the injectors recently
It comes with a new stereo, including bluetooth mic for hands-free phone calls

The Bad:
There is some minor fender damage, I tried to show in the picture (near rear passenger-side door).  It was like that when I bought it.  Hardly noticeable.
The seats are starting to give out.  This is extremely common with this car at it's age.  Personally doesn't bother me, but you might need to add some cushion at some point.
Needs a new A/C belt.  If frayed last year so I cut it off because...
Needs the A/C recharged.  The A/C motor and vacuum switch still actually work, but there is no juice inside.
The climate control has issues.  This is the only real issue with the car as far as I'm concerned.  At this point let's just say that it does not have a functional heating/cooling system.  (That's not entirely accurate, as it can be made to wrok, it's just a huge pain and very finnicky, so better to just say it's inoperable).   If I had time this would be the first thing I addressed on this car.  
Oh yeah--the hood ornament came off, but I still have it.  Looks like an easy enough fix but bodywork-type stuff is not my forte.

So anyways there you have it.  I hope you can make a nice home for this awesome ride.  It really drives like no other car I've ever been in--come take a look!

It also comes with a service agreement that's good through November 2018 and is still under factory warranty for both bumper to bumper and powertrain (the shocks didn't void the warranty). 

I get about 17.5 - 18mpg with the wheels that are on it driving 30/70 city/hwy. 

This is a smoke free, pet free, kid free vehicle. I just had the 15k service done. 

No, it doesn't have leather.
No, it doesn't have a moonroof.
No, to doesn't have JBL speakers. 
No, it doesn't turn into a helicopter.  

I'm looking for $35, 250 

If you want to make a offer, feel free.
This price is well within KBB for private party purchase so, LOWBALLS WILL BE IGNORED and, I won't respond to "what's the lowest you'll take". 

Not interested in trades.

Title: 1990 Ford F150 Lariat XLT 302 5.0L V8 Automatic 4x4
Description:
For sale or trade. 1990 Ford F150 Lariat XLT. Automatic transmission with the 302 5.0L V8. 4x4. Here's the rundown:

I traded my car that needed a rebuilt engine for this truck. I wasn't looking for a truck (which is why I'm selling/trading) but couldn't turn down a running vehicle for a non-running one when the trade was offered. 
I was told the 97,000 on the odometer is accurate and it hasn't rolled over, but I have no way to verify. Supposedly was used mainly to tow a pop-up tent trailer.

The good-
*Engine, transmission and 4x4 in great shape. 
*New tires (see pics)
*New deep cycle big boy battery (see pic)
*Bed liner (see pic)
*Dual gas tanks (see pic)
*New plugs, wires, solenoid
*Replaced throttle position sensor yesterday
*Tow package wired for trailer brakes (see pics)
*16 mpg on highway even with V8 thanks to Overdrive 
*Clean interior, seats in good condition in front and back (see pics)
*Highly sought after year/make/model, rarer short bed, extended cab 4x4 combo is hard to find 
*Clean clear title in hand
*Will include pair of steel ramps (see pic)

The bad
*Brake booster and/or master cylinder need replaced (under $150 for parts at autozone, see pics. Even cheaper at pick-a-part). Brakes work, (drove it home) but pedal is stiff, and you can hear vacuum line from failing booster when you press the pedal. Will need addressed, but cheap and easy fix, even if taken to a shop.
*Paint isn't great in a few spots, a couple small dents, but it is a 29 year old truck.
*Left door speaker will need replaced (have a random spare I can include if you want it)
*Not current on registration, last registered through 7/17. Has 30 day trip permit, expired (6/24). Eligible for another permit at DMV though if you don't want to register immediately.

This is a highly sought after truck, you won't find one this year/make/model in this good of running condition for this price, feel free to try. Ford should put them back in production, imo.
All the big stuff (4x4, engine, tranny) is ready to go. Priced for quick sale to get me back into a daily driver. 

If I fix the small stuff it'll be listed for $4875 (NADA mid-range evaluation with all options, see pic) Low end is $2448, get it at a steal before the next guy. This is an awesome truck that will only take a little TLC to make it an amazing truck.
 
No holds, no delivery outside of Lebanon. Trades possible, let me know what you've got. Must be daily driver of equal value, or you add cash on top. Don't need help selling. Cash only, no money order, cashier's check or crypto. Must use CL email relay, unfortunately receive too many scams when listing number, sorry (a few bad apples on here). I will be happy to call or text once I can tell you are a real person who is actually interested. 
Happy hunting.

Title: Nissan Maxima
Description: This 2001 Nissan Maxima 20th Anniversary Edition has been my daily driver for the last 2 years. It has some issues but does the job, I recently bought a new car and am ready to move on from this one. It has a clean title and the odometer reads 180000 miles. We have replaced the front axles, transmission pan, and it has an entirely new starter and brand new battery. The car has after market halo lights, an after market exhaust, coil over lowering springs, and a cold air intake. It also has fairly new tires with good tread. There is a dent on the front drivers side fender and the driver side window needs a new motor. The interior is very clean and the car has all the original carpets. The "Service Engine Soon" light has been on the entire time I have owned the car and the entire time the previous owner had the car, an OBD scan will tell you to replace the O2 sensor, it's never caused me any noticeable issue.

Title: 2010 Mustang GT Low miles

Not interested in any trades. $13500 only.  Willing to haggle on the price.

Title: Dodge Ram Longhorn 4x4
Description:
My wife needs a new ride, just lowered the price again. Buy this before someone else does. Beautiful Laramie Longhorn SE with matching canopy. This is a special western run numbered 244 of 500. There is no KBB listing on this unit. It is priced now below recommended book price for above average vehicles. This price is firm, I've dropped it down where it is more than reasonable. 

I'm downsizing as my wife won't drive it, says "we" need to get something else. There is nothing wrong with it in any way shape or form. I'm the second owner and it's very low miles for a six year old vehicle. I researched the NW, Autotrader, eBay motors, and a lot of other places and there is no rig anywhere that compares with it for any  price. A new one of this class would run over 80K, why buy new? This one has the bugs out of it and runs beautiful. I have a complete vehicle report available with request. It's never been wrecked, use the VIN to run a Carfax if you want but it's explained in the report I've already paid for.

It's a non smoking rig and the interior is like new, full grain leather with Longhorn logos on seats, floor mats, and the saddle bags behind the seats. It is a deep clear coat white with gold accent and trim, and it is custom pinstriped on both truck and canopy with the number on the side. 

As for options, it has every option available plus some aftermarket goodies too. This 5.7 Hemi engine is extremely powerful, I added a Flowmaster exhaust system and a K and N air cleaner, the mileage improved to about 14 city and 19 highway, and also increased the performance. The usual accessories for a luxury rig, PS, PB, 6 way seats, heated seats front and rear, cooled front, pwr windows around, sun roof, adjustable pedals, built in brake system and self leveling system for trailer hauling (it's never hauled heavy), factory installed navigation system, large 8" screen with GPS, AM/FM/, CD and Sirius XM radio, UConnect, multiple USB ports, 110 outlet, premium Alpine sound system, back up camera and alarm, custom 20" wheels and good tires, locking lug nuts for theft protection, 6 speed manual/automatic, under seat storage in rear and hidden storage under floor in rear, blown in bedliner, grille guard, bug deflector, and it's regularly maintained, I use Mobile 1 long drain. It was maintained by the dealer for the first year and a half and my local mechanic until now. 

The title is held by Selco Credit Union and any money transfer will be bank to bank for the protection of both parties. Sorry, no PayPal, been there done that, and as stated earlier, no trades. I don't know if I missed anything but if you have questions, drop an email to the g mail place, acrocker38 and I'll try to answer them. This won't last long at this price, be the proud new owner.

Title: Nissan Sentra se 5 speed
Description: Good little 2001 Nissan Sentra se. Runs and drives. Check engine light says it needs a noc sensor. And if you stall it it continues stalling until that sensor resets. Also does this if you turn it off and then turn it back on before 30 min or so. When it does this it requires two footing it, so your foot is always on the gas. Part costs about 80 bucks. Drivers side window needs wires replaced (20 bucks online and some time) so it won't roll down or up, and is stuck at 1\4 the way down. Some wear and damage to interior and light scratches and a few dents to exterior. Dash lights are out, but we installed new momentary with red lights. Once these parts are fixed itd be a good car for a teen. $950 OBO.

Title: 1990 jeep Cherokee xj long arm
Description:
I have had this for about 15 years but I've upgraded so it's time for it to go.
 '90 Cherokee with '93 HO 4.0l, 5 speed ax15 manual Tranny, 231 transfer case, Ford Explorer 8.8 rear with locker, d30 front with the larger abs  axle shafts, about 6" of lift with long arms up front, reinforced steering gear box, 33 12.50 15 on 8" wide steel wheels. 
Engine runs good, doesn't burn oil. Tranny shifts good. Tcase and axles are sound. 
It's mostly been a wheeling rig for the past decade with little daily driving, so it's pretty rough. You could daily drive it but it's best suited as a trail rig. I can tell you everything that I've done to it and everything it needs.
 I have an extra d30 with otk steering, roof rack, rear rack, other wheels/tires, spare np231, and the old engine. All of which could be negotiated or sold separately. possible part trade/trade. Dirt bike, kids quad, little fishing boat, cvt roof tent...
 Motivated to sell

1986 Toyota Corolla
Description:
1986 Toyota Corolla. Body is impeccable shape, and so is the interior. Very clean car overall, and I believe it is missing only 1 thing: the muffler. Everything else should be there. All 4 original hubcaps are there, and tires have good tread. It even has the original green jack stand bag and spare tire, etc. I have a clean title too!

So what's the catch??? Blown motor. This car does not run. I was told the motor was overheated as the previous owner was driving around with the upper radiator hose detached for quite some time. If you have a motor to drop in that's excellent. Likewise, rebuild kits for the engine are less than $300. Also, could be parted out and some money made there as well. Lot's of options given the nice condition of the vehicle.

I am open to delivering, depending on where you are and what kind of a delivery fee we can agree on. Car is currently located near Dallas, OR. Down to $400 OBO.

Title: 1992 Subaru Outback (Legacy)
Description:
I acquired this Outback from a family friend after helping them buy a newer one. I was hoping to use this in the Gambler 500, but alas, I am not free that weekend!

The good: low miles (for a sub), good tires, clean interior (no big rips or stains), doesn't appear to leak or burn oil, new CV axles, trans fluid looks great and trans work fine, power steering is great, power windows functional, all lighting works; starts, runs, and drives just fine.

The Bad: small exhaust leak, weak battery, missing two hub caps, looks like hell on the outside, ruptured rear brake lines.

For those that know Outbacks, you know that there are plenty of great condition parts on this car. Engine is really in fine shape, and the trans appears to be great as well. Really, the appearance is the most negative thing (a plus in the Gambler 500 though), and the ruptured brake line make driving home dicey. The brakes were fine when I picked it up, and actually ruptured along the way home. Just my luck!

If I can't sell this rather quickly, I will go ahead and fix a few things on it, and clean it up a bit. There is a LOT of good car here, with lower miles. Come get it while the getting is good!

Title: Ford Bronco '82  302 V8  4x4  New Engine & Carb + More
Description:
Everything about the truck is listed below. If interested send an email with your phone number/ name and put "BRONCO" in the subject line so I can get back to you ASAP. I need the truck until about the end of July. Asking $3500 or best offer. Please feel free to make an offer, don't be shy. Please only inquire if you're a serious buyer.

I am the second owner of this 1982 Ford Bronco 4x4 that I have put a lot of work into it. I am moving out of state and unfortunately cannot take it with me. It's a great reliable rig. I've been driving it every day for 6 years to school/ work and back. I typically drive about 5K miles/ year, so it still has low miles on it. Regularly take it in for maintenance, transmission flush, radiator flush, tire rotation, brake fluid, oil change every 3K miles and top it off in between. 

****** Features: ******

302 V8 5.0L Engine, Double barrel carb (I have the original sales receipt from the first owner)
Original engine replaced at 102K miles (Odometer has rolled over since it only goes up to 99,999 miles, 32K on the new engine (I have the original paperwork and warranty from the first owner)
4-wheel drive (works great)
Captain's chairs 
Full-size spare (swing away)
Truck mirrors
32 Gallon fuel tank
High output heater
Rear spoiler 
Halogen lights
Fiberglass top (removable convertible)
Fold down rear seat (removable)
Extra set of rims (4 rims that match the full-size spare rim in case you want to switch out for snow or mud tires mid-season)
All lights and signals work
Includes Chilton Manual

****** Since I've had it, replaced (I still have the paperwork for most of this): ******

New Carburetor & mount spacer
New brake booster & master cylinder 
New front tie rods & alignment 
New Tires (all season and good tread)
Complete Front brake job, new rear brake cylinders (all bearings packed and greased)
Headcover gaskets & stem seals 
Mechanical fuel pump
New CRV valve
Belts, hoses, and full tune up
Transmission screen replacement and transmission service
Plugs and Plug cables
New oil drain plug
 
In the last few months replaced:
Dura spark module for distributor
Cap and rotor
Battery and terminal cable
New tags (good for 2 years)
Tire rotation
Cell phone holder with audio cable which links into the AM/FM sound system (Spotify ready!)

****** It has a few kinks to it: ******

Back window needs a new pin for the electric motor's gear and won't roll down using the switch until it gets fixed (Quoted $100 to fix by a local auto body shop and the motor is fine)

Has been bumped two different times in low-speed fender benders on the passenger side in front of and behind the door. The damage is purely aesthetic and does not affect the performance or function. 

Stereo is a 100-watt amp Pioneer tape deck, tape deck is broken but the radio works great, and I use a radio transmitter to link it to my cell phone for music and navigation.

No AC (The first owner chose to not have one installed. It's fine on hot days when you open the windows/ fins/ and floor vents.)

Title: Reliable Commuter - 2005 Kia Spectra
Description:
2005 KIA SPECTRA EX - 158K Miles - Manual Transmission

This is a reliable commuter car in good mechanical condition. I've owned this for 6 years and put 65K miles on it including driving across the state nearly 2 dozen times. It's a comfortable vehicle and I've never been concerned about whether it would start or its reliability while driving. 

Consistent light maintenance has been performed on the vehicle (oil changes, spark plugs, tire changes, replacement of brake pads, lights, wipers, fluid changes etc.) Its largest maintenance job was performed recently: the brake light limit switch was shorted and draining the battery. During the troubleshoot and repair process I replaced the broken switch, battery and alternator (they were getting old), alternator belt, and AC compressor belt. 

You can expect a working, reliable, and relatively fuel-efficient car (~22/30 mpg). There are no serious issues and over the next 50K miles will probably require only minor repairs. 

There are a few known issues. Most of these are either cosmetic or on auxiliary systems. 
- The windshield wiper spray system is not working. This is most likely due to clogged lines or a damaged pump. 
- Light scratches and dents in a few places - hood of the car, rear, etc. 
- The driver-side door must be locked manually. Some of the gears on the door's auto-lock are damaged and make a grinding sound.

Please call or text Scott at the CL # listed.

Title: 2001 Ford Ranger
Description:
I have a 2001 Ford ranger. Regular cab. 
4.0 V6. Two wheel drive. Craftsman toolbox included. Great little truck. Definitely responds when you put your foot in to it. It has just over 146k on it. It used to be a Seattle city truck and was always kept up on maintanence. And I have always rountinely stayed current on the oil and kept it in good condition. There is a little bit of wear on the driver side seat from getting in and out and there is a little bit of the paint that started to peel at the top of the cab. Other than that, it's in perfect condition. This was my daily driver for the last four years, but I upgraded to a full size, so I don't need it anymore. 

Call/ Text anytime

Title: 1974 f-100
Description:
1974 f100 Super cab 2wd.  
Truck has a 390 with a c6 behind it and a 9" reared.
Power Steering and power disc brakes.
This truck has been off the road since 2001. Just installed a new battery and Last year I replaced the fuel pump and rebuilt the carb. I also installed a new master cylinder, front cailipers and flushed out all the old brake fluid. The truck runs drives, stops and turns, but needs a little more work to be daily driven. Bed floor is rusty and bottom of passenger door is rusted out. My parents bought the truck back in 1987 and at some point lost the title, I have all the lost title paper work filled out and ready to go.

$2000 OBO Not interested in trades

Title: 2014 Ford Escape SE
Description:
This car has served us well for the past 3 years, however with a new child on the way we have outgrown it at last. Aside from regular oil changes, the only work that we have had to do on it was replace a wheel bearing when it started making noise. That was done by an ASE certified mechanic.

This car features:
 - EcoBoost Turbo for improved power and fuel efficiency (22 - 25 in town, 24 - 28 on the highway)
 - Automatic 4WD kicks in only when you need it for safe handling on wet or snowy roads
 - Panoramic sun roof
 - Microsoft Sync interface allows phone and audio integration with iOS and Android devices (Bluetooth and USB, including charging)
 - Fully adjusting and telescoping steering column
 - 5-way adjustable power driver's seat with inflatable lumbar support provides a comfortable ride for any driver

Title: 2003 GMC Yukon XL 4wd
Description:
I have a 2003 GMC Yukon XL in good condition. It can easily seat 4 or 5 people with a gigantic cargo space in the rear.  I have had it for more than two years and it has never had any major issues. A/C recently fixed and Heat works good. Alternator and battery have been replaced since I have owned it. I bought new tires when I first got it so they have about 54k miles on them. I consider this a truck and not an SUV because it can tow more than 8,000 lbs like a truck. It has automatic 4 wheel drive. The interior is in okay condition with exception of the leather on the drivers seat and some of the fabric on the ceiling is loose.

The mileage reads 354k. My uncle who previously owned it was in the military and drove it back and forth from Georgia to Alabama. I listed the price to reflect that.  Otherwise, I have found it to be a reliable vehicle.

Description:
Please review to the bottom before contacting me, greatly appreciated.
1931 Model A 2 door Sports Coupe
Top and door frames have been chopped 4.5 inches 
Carson removable soft top, steel frame but not welded together yet, custom made
Rumble seat
Steel floor pans, they are new, not bolted but set in place and fitted, holes cut for tranny

Frame and suspension modified and dropped 14 in the front(split wishbone drop) and 9 in the back
Breaks, axles, wheel bearings, tranny all rebuilt, entire chassis has been blasted and restored
Rims have been gloss black powdercoated and straightened, not in picture but same style, with wide white walls
Good running 4 cylinder flat head, has new exhaust header(custom made), custom intake manifold started, new Stromberg 97 Carb w/beehive air cleaner, high compression police cylinder head, 
Have all parts to finish car and new parts with exception of upholstery.  75 % done.
Current theme is 30's hot rod.  Very unique build so far.

Possible trade but looking to sell outright as shop space is necessity.  NO BIKES, Im good.  Price is firm so if truly interested call me.  Please pay attention to the "firm", if you want a remarkable project come get it but respect that I won't ask you to pay more so don't ask me to take less.  

I don't need help selling and no solicitations.  Serious inquiries and interest only please.  Not interested in parting out so if you only want the body it is $16,000.

Title: 2001 Chevy Chevrolet Venture LT Maroon Minivan Runs Great, Reliable
Description:
I have a decent condition 2001 Chevy Venture. We treated this car well and it runs great, clean, never had a problem, oil changed regularly.  2 keys, 2 remote fobs. Very reliable, seats 7.

SERIOUS PURCHASERS ONLY: No reseller calls. No low ballers, tire kickers, etc.

CALL  
  
 To get my email address, take out both (remove) from the previous. Thanks, Rick.

It is the LT version which includes a few nice options: roof racks, power side door, back up sensor, temp display/compass, more

A few issues are that the AC condenser has a pinhole leak so it will not cool and the drivers side 2nd row captain's chair armrest bolt has stripped out of the chair. Airbag light is on - I am working on fixing that. Driver's seat is power but slow, could just need lube, not sure. Drivers side view mirror power function is down. Does burn a little oil and it does leak a little bit of oil, but not enough to drip on the driveway - has not been  problem for me for the last several years.

It is a great basic car for transportation and hauling you name it. You can take the seats out and put a washer/dryer, fridge, 4x8 plywood in there.

See more specifications here:

edmunds.com/chevrolet/venture/2001/st-100000716/features-specs/

Vehicle Summary:

The 2001 Chevrolet Venture targeted the family transportation market, offering a full-size passenger van with a roomy interior and a range of trims. Buyers could choose from a basic Value Edition, the more upscale LS, the LT, and the high-end Plus. The Warner Brothers Edition, which combined luxury touches with an integrated video entertainment system, was another trim option; the LS, LT, and Plus models were available in both regular and extended-wheelbase versions.

In addition to passenger space and cargo capacity, the '01 Chevy Venture had solidity and power to recommend it. A 4.6-liter V6 engine with 185 horsepower and 210 lb.-ft. of torque gave the 2001 Venture plenty of zip for a larger van. And it did so without sacrificing fuel efficiency entirely: An EPA estimate of 18 mpg city, 25 mpg highway compares favorably to other vans in its class.

My lease is up in a month on my 2015 Chevy Silverado. Going to try to sell it in that time, otherwise Ill just be giving it back to the dealership

-LT Z71 5.3L ecotec3 v8 Crew Cab with 49.5k miles
-4x4

Comes with the Plus Package and all star package

-Deep ocean blue color.
-4" chromed running boards
-8"touchscreen 
-Backup camera
-Onstar navigation system (only with onstar subscription)
-Dual climate control
-Powered drivers seat
-Bench front seat with fold down middle console
-Power sliding rear window
-All weather mats
-Remote start
-Premium Line-x spray in Berliner
-EZ-lift and lower tailgate
-Tinted windows
-Power heated outside mirrors
-Leather wrapped steering wheel
-Bluetooth and cruise control commands integrated into steering wheel
-USB ports in center console
-Hill start assist system
-Electronically Adjustable brake/accelerator pedals

The truck has had regular service and has been a complete pavement princess. I'm the original owner.

It could use a new set of tires but they still have some tread left.

Text or email only please

Title: 1975 CJ5 with AMC 360
Description:
1975 Jeep CJ5
Fresh AMC 360 swapped in for original AMC 304
New Edelbrock 1826 650 CFM off-road carb (only run clear gas in this Jeep)
DANA 44 with limited slip
DANA 30 with open knuckles
DANA 20 transfer case
T15 3 spd
Partially boxed frame
New skyjacker shocks all around
Soft top and full doors
Body and paint are ok for age
Electrical is good
5x like new 31 BFG ATs with excellent tread
Swing out tire carrier
Clean title
Good at highway speed (up to 70mph)
Power steering
No radio, just the rumble of 360 cubic inches of American muscle
15 gallon fuel tank

Great driving Jeep that could be cherry with some Bondo and paint. Tracks straight, eats steep hills for breakfast. Awesome summer time driver that does well in snow, mud, rocks, etc. Would make an excellent wheeler, restoration candidate, or daily driver. Mechanically sound and reliable, and extremely capable off-road.

Open to trades for other off-road vehicles, classic cars, dirt bikes, other guy stuff. Trades should be of equal value for consideration.

Description:

Title: 2003 Suburban 2500
Description:
2003 Suburban 2500 LT

Hard to find 3/4 ton Suburban. Pretty much loaded. 8.1L V8
Front row bucket seats. Middle row captains chairs. Third row bench. All leather. Seats seven. Bose stereo with waveguide subwoofer, sunroof, cruise pretty much every option available for that year. 

This thing is born to tow, electric trailer mirrors, four wheel disk brakes, 4:10 gears, engine braking, seven wire towing plug with inertia brake controller and wired to charge. Flow master exhaust with a K&N air filter. 12,000lb towing capacity. 

This thing has been awesome and we love it. It took us two years to find it, and right after we purchased it, we got pregnant with baby number 5. We used it to tow our 20' toyhauler to Suttle Lake last summer and is was an incredible improvement over our previous half ton Suburban (with respect to towing). We have since sold our toyhauler, had baby number 5, and decided that we are not going to tow anything for a couple years. We purchased a full size passenger van and no longer using this Suburban for its intended purpose. 

This thing is a beast and seriously fun to drive. The previous owner was a GM dealership mechanic who took super good care of it. It has a recently (within the last two years) rebuilt transmission and a file folder full of maintenance records. The front seats have been re-upholstered with factory leather and the heating element was replaced on the driver's side. 

That being said, it has a couple of gremlins. 

It is my understanding that all of these things can be traced back to a single item, but I have not replace it. It is called the seat memory module, or something to that effect. 
-The heated seats on the driver's side do not stay on.
-The clock randomly resets.
-The heating and cooling settings for the front are not accurate. (Room temperature seems to equate to about 84 degrees on the setting).
-The windows seem to stop working from time to time. 
Ironically, the two memory positions for the driver's seat, pedals, and mirrors, seem to hold for the most part. 
-At some point, someone struck something with the passenger mirror and the "up and down" adjustment does not work remotely. 

Outside of those items, it runs and drives perfect. It does have somewhat knobby tires (that I do not like but my wife loves) that are a bit noisey on the road.

We have road tripped this thing up to Vancouver Island. It is a road warrior for sure. It will not cover ground quite like a half ton, mostly due to the lower gearing, and it does not get fantastic gas mileage, but it has a massive amount of torque, phenomenal passing power, and recognizes no type of topography. Sans trailer, it does not even shift out of overdrive to climb hills at highway speeds. The front suspension is super tight, and it actually handles quite well for something that weighs over 7000 lbs. 

Honestly, its kind of hard to let this thing go, but such is life. We are very aware of how difficult it is to find this particular Suburban configuration, so please don't waste anyone's time with low ball offers. The transaction will take place at my bank as I still owe some money on this fella (I've owned it for just over a year) so that would mean you would need cash or a cashier's check or something to that effect.

Title: 2006 Nissan Titan LE 4x4

Look up the specs on the deck. I paid $500 when it came out. So yes, it does most everything. Bluetooth, DVD, etc. Compustar remote start with 2 remotes. Full interior LED upgrade including all 4 door vanity lights. Weathertech floor mats. ARE canopy w/ keys. Truck is an LE model so it's pretty loaded for the year. Spent $1000 on all new brakes about 4 months ago. Have receipt. I believe the tint is 18% all the way around. Rear parking sensors. Banks exhaust. Interior is 9/10, paint is 7/10. Title: 1996 Chevrolet Silverado 1500 4x4
Description:
I am selling my 1996 Chevrolet Silverado. I've owned this truck for 7 years and have just recently purchased a newer vehicle. Truck is in fair shape. No leaks of any kind and since I've had it I've replaced many parts to keep it operational. Repairs include:
New 5 speed transmission (20k miles on it)
New radiator (15k miles on it)
replacement gaskets for exhaust output.
replacement of oil cooling lines.
I have paperwork for all listed repairs and have had additional work which i have not listed. This truck is certainly not in perfect condition but the interior is clean, the engine runs strong, and has a clean title. Call/text/email if interested. pictures coming soon!

Title: 1995 Chevy S10
Description:
This is a nice little reliable pickup. It will fit your needs for whatever you're doing. Are you a student who needs a cheap reliable ride? Someone who needs a truck for around the farm? Or somebody just looking for a good pickup to haul dirt bikes in or something. This is it. This pickup is very reliable and runs extremely good. It has a brand new alternator. A brand new clutch that was done about 2,000 miles ago. The head gasket was done a year ago and it has nearly brand new tires as well as good tags through July 2019. It also has brand new spark plugs and spark plug wires. Just put bed liner in it as well! 
      The only problems it has are the dings and scrapes of a 23 year old pickup and a small transmission leak. I took it to a shop to get it fixed and the mechanic said to just get the transmission fluid topped off when you get your oil changed and you're good to go!! Come give it a ride. It's a good pickup and it will last you until you get something nicer. Helped me out when I needed a solid ride. Made it even more reliable. And now I am in a better spot and got a new car and it's time for the old pickup to help somebody else. This pickup will not break down on you!!

Salvage title in my name. Previous owner backed into a fence. Has a new tailgate. No problems other than what I stated.  


Available for a test drive anytime! 2.3 LT 2WD Manual. About 25 MPG.

Title: Pro-street built 1987 Chevrolet Corvette
Description:
Well, I gotta pay for college somehow so here it is.

I am selling my black automatic 1987 Corvette. This muscle car will shake your house while idling outside, but also needs mild restoration so choosing a price is really hard. At the end of the day I need the money so give me your offers.

Pros: The car was built by a previous owner roughly ten years ago, and the fact that it has always been reliable to me is a testament it is done well. I've also done some restoring since I bought the car as it needed it. What exactly is under the valve covers is a bit of a pandora's box but here is my best attempt at a description:
-Complete service history for last 4 years
-1 Year transmission warranty god through 5/2019 from Advance Transmission Service in Eugene. I have this in writing. Transmission went out just recently as they tend to do at 120k but new one works great.
-52mm BBK dual throttle body
-super aggressive cam. See google drive link.
-K&N filter
-Flowmasters
-Cat delete
-Just did rear main seal, car does not leak oil
-All new weatherstripping two years ago, I have been keeping this greased for long life
-New windshield, last one had rock chips
-Updated late C4 wheels
-New rear tires, wont need tires front or back for at least 10k miles

Cons: This car is a ten thousand dollar car, but it just needs work I can't do. This is why it is at the price it is.
-Has a "ten foot" paint job. Beautiful blue-black metallic but wasn't clear-coated.
-Had the car parked for three months while waiting for a transmission and now they're really bad.
-Antenna missing since I bought it. Radio still worked fine.
-Had an aftermarket stereo but when I put the stock one back in I must've missed a wire since it doesn't turn on.
-Speedometer screen is burning out.
-Hood scoop had a broken fastener and was loose so I took it off.

Anyway, I wanna be as transparent as possible and make sure both of us are happy with the sale.

To see a short video of the car I took last week, click the link. 
https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B8BVKRrWELfKU2RDUVdGWjZxSXNjRnhTdkdxdlZSaUwxY2RZ

I will also be entering it at the Hope Church car show on 6/17 so come by to see it or at the least make an offer before as I'mm going to find a buyer there. 

Contact me (Josiah) at  
 (texting okay) or via email at

Title: 1999 Pontiac Firebird Graduation or Bucket List Gift
Description:
Fixed by Mechanic so I am Reposting due to P0300 code/Multiple Missing Cylinders.  

I bought this Firebird last July to go on Hwy 101 down the coast to my aunts who lives in Ventura, CA for my 60th birthday bucket list item: Drive a convertible down Hwy 101. Check. Coincidentally, the guy I bought it from had done the same thing with his wife just a month before me. He bought it from a guy in Bend, OR who had it for most of its life. The tires were checked so I replaced them before my trip and had the air conditioning fixed. Oil change before my trip and even though it's been less than 3000 miles, I'll do a full synthetic oil change again. It is a 5 speed, 6 cylinder engine and drives like a dream. I got 25-29 mpg on my trip. It's a wonderful car, I hate to sell it, but it needs to become someone else's dream car now. It is in Excellent shape and only has 81,750 miles. Yes, you heard me right, only 81,750 miles and counting. I don't know if you know it, but GM 6 cylinders are one of the most reliable engines made. Since it is a 1999, it is also a lot easier to work on if you are so inclined. Don't miss out on this car, reminiscent of the muscle cars of a bygone era. You won't regret it.

Title: 1994 Dodge Ram 2500 Laramie SLT
Description: 1994 Dodge Ram 2500 , 5.9 V-8 Gas, Automatic, 3/4 ton Pickup. I have all records - every detail - since I started driving it with 2 miles on the odometer. 238000 meticulously maintained miles.  I am reluctant to sell this truck as it has been the most reliable vehicle I have ever driven in my 50 years on the road, and it has by far, the best Air Conditioning of ANY vehicle I have ever been in. Runs today as good as the first day I drove it. I have changed the oil over 60 times. Planned on keeping it forever, so I have a pickup load of new in the boxes -parts ($800)for future maintenance IE: Oil filters , front brake discs, front wheel bearings, rear brake shoes, all rear brake parts , windshield wiper motor, set of used 17 inch tires and wheels, and lots more new parts. In the last year (3000 Miles) I have newly installed : Radiator $250, Turn Signal -windshield washer Switch $95, Headlight Switch $53, front Brake Pads $20, 10 ply tires $900, Battery $96 and more. Has lifetime spray in bed liner installed when new  at 200 miles, Transmission Cooler installed at 100 miles, Class IV Hitch Receiver installed when it was a month old. Truck is in good shape with the only body mark is the dent in the passenger door as seen in the pictures. As typical for all the 94 thru 96 trucks the paint started peeling, Once a year I spend a day touching it up. The interior is great, the seats have never been sat on, always had seat covers, ( I rolled them back, to see, in the pictures). Stainless Steel tie downs on the bed. Has some unique Features : I Designed , Fabricated and Installed a Sealed Ram Air , Cold Air Intake with K&N air filter (as seen in the pictures under the front bumper and in the engine compartment) that increased horse power and the mileage range to over 600 miles per tank of gas. Lots more to show off . I would not hesitate to climb in, this morning, and haul a load to Boston and back.  There is gas in the tank. Title: 2002 Toyota Camry - runs great.
Description:
Upgraded to a newer vehicle so it's time to sell the old Camry, it's been a great car. I bought this about 2 years ago and it had around 120,00 miles on it. I've ran it up to almost 143,00 since then. 

The engine and transmission (5 speed manual) are in good shape and the car runs great. A few months ago I drove it from Texas to Missouri to Oregon without any issues. AC and heater work. Radio and CD player work, and I've got a little bluetooth device in it that lets you connect your phone to the radio - stays with the car. 

Just put 4 brand new tires on the car in January - bought at Costco in Albany. See attached screen shot. Put in a new battery, November 2017. Replaced all spark plugs and a bad engine coil last summer. Had the catalytic converter and O2 sensors replaced almost 2 years ago, so that takes care of the most expensive items that tend to go wrong with these cars. 

No current mechanical issues with the vehicle that I am aware of, but it's a 2002 so little things have to be fixed every now and then. No issues with brakes. The biggest downside to the car is the paint. The person I purchased the car from had a cheap paint job done and it's showing now, flecking off in places. The rear window tint is also bubbling and it makes it difficult to see out of at times. There are small stains in the carpet and on the back seat. Also, it's missing one hubcap. I've attached relevant pictures. 

Bottom line - car runs great, I have the title in hand, and it's a reliable vehicle.

Feel free to come give it a test drive. I'm usually off of work by 5 pm M-F, may be able to meet earlier than that on Tuesday's. Email me from Craigslist or text is fine. 

This car has a 5-speed MANUAL transmission.

Description: 61 ford fairlane one of a kind! was 4dr. now 2dr. gasser style. Straight axle, rack & pinion. all steel hyd. tilt front. painted like cop car. has working old school siren, bubble gum light, rear strobes, front reds,w/alternating headlights, has external speakers in front, plays theme song from cops! Called "Da Fuzz" Heres the Oh S#*T factor. has 472 caddy eldorado eng and trans, under back window! And, will do wheelie w/ease, anytime you want! No BS. has some extra weight in trunk, so it will do low speed wheelies, arrow straight, under control, w/o thrashing it. And when you let off, comes down soft. but I have also dragged the tailpipes for 100ft+ down the road! cln title. 100% street legal. runs sweet, not a sports car, but drives better than you expect.  recent new carb, electronic ign. valve covers. recent all new rear bearings/brakes, all new tires. all this has less than 300 mi.   car is a blast to drive. If you dont like being center of attention, and talking about your car a lot, its not for you. This bad boy draws a crowd  Everywhere it goes!. Unique major head turner, show stopper. I have been parked next to 100k show cars, and have had them move, because all eyes were on "Da Fuzz"! took to over 25 shows, and won 15 1st place trophies, the rest 2nd, or most unique! you will never park next to another one, anywhere! Only problem it has, is when you drive it, your face starts hurting, from constantly smiling! if interested in car, can send before pics of build, and heres link to video of it in action!    https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Okk0iC42Kos  Shes not perfect, but is well built, and has done dozens of wheel stands, over last several years, with no major problems! ALSO. Last pics show what it started as, and some of build pics, so you can see time and effort, and how well its built. Car is now being stored in Southern Ore. but still has clean WA title, and WA perm plate. Last Chance to own a one of a kind ride. If you never have, let me tell you, Wheelies are Bitchin Fun!! LOOK! working on new property, and need cash for building supplies ASAP, so right now, Was $9500, One Time Deal. 1st $6850 Cash, FIRM. Not One Cent Less.  takes! Can deliver for fuel costs! Mildly built transmission with billet, single disc torque converter, tuned valve body capable of locking the torque converter in all forward gears, and finned aluminum transmission pan.  Mag-hytec rear differential cover.  Front trailer hitch receiver, 2".  Comes with a fiberglass canopy and/or aluminum diamond plate, cross-rail toolbox.
$14,900 OBO.  
In person transactions only. Cash or cashiers check. 
Will consider part trade of flatbed gooseneck trailer 14 k or higher weight rating or tractor implements.

Title: PARTS CAR! - 1993 Honda Accord
Description: PARTS CAR! This car is a great little runner but unfortunately I was told by my mechanic that it has a compression problem. I had a friend look at the car and he said the compression problem could possibly be a head gasket or piston ring burn out. This car had a refurbished Honda engine installed in 2015. Fairly new tires and transmission. Everything else is mostly up to date. This car does burn through oil fairly quickly and just needs oil to be added periodically. Other than a few aesthetic quirks, this little car is great and would be a great project car. I'm sad to part with it but I'm moving out of the country and hope someone else can put it to good use.

Title: 2009 Ford Focus SE (White/Clean/Economical)
Description:
Selling a 2009 Ford Focus SE, automatic transmission, clean title, white color for $4000. It runs great, I have used it mainly for transit between Eugene and Corvallis for the past year. The sound system is excellent, it's my favorite part about the car. I recently got the front tires rebalanced, but otherwise no service has been done on it while I have owned it. It's had two previous owners before me, and I have only had it for a year, adding ~7000 miles on it. Driving both city and highway has it around 30~mpg (The dash shows both your mpg and how many miles you have until empty), and it has never failed me. 

The SYNC Sound System does Bluetooth, USB, and aux line in. I personally like to charge my iPhone while utilizing the Bluetooth. The outside is a little bit dirty, but overall not in bad shape. I had a little mishap doing a catering job for an Indian restaurant last summer, and as a result there is some curry stains in the trunk. It doesn't smell, nor affect anything, and I'll do my best to clean it up before the final transaction.

Title: 2000 Toyota Land Cruiser
Description:
2000 Toyota Land Cruiser.

I've got 4 mounted snow tires that can be added to the deal too. They've only got like 15,000 miles at most. 

Cent diff locker, power door locks, power windows, power leather seats in fantastic condition, sun roof, CD player, USB/stereo plug for phone, AC blows cold, heated seats. 

New headlights. 
New wipers. 
New starter. 
New rear trim pieces. 
New front fog lamps. 
Newer brakes and calipers (2016) 
Oil just changed. 
Timing belt replaced. 
Clean CarFax report. 

This thing is a tank and will drive you up and over any mountain and around town in style. I've got multiple friends still driving Land Cruisers with over 750,000 miles on them. This rig is one of the most reliable vehicles ever produced.

Drivers seat in great shape.
Priced to sell, serious inquiries only please. 

Selling bc I need much larger truck for hauling equipment.

Title: 2003 Dodge Durango 157k mi. 4.7L v8 magnum! *3 row seating*
Description:
Selling my pretty clean 03 Durango with 157k on it. Runs strong and shifts smooth! 4x4 works great hi and lo. Has flow master exhaust, Ken wood stereo and pioneer speakers, 3 rows of seating(holds 8) great for a family or someone who likes more room. Tags are brand new and good thru 2020. Newer tires and brakes too. I've changed the oil every 4K miles with fully synthetic and always maintained it. Ever since the day I bought it one lifter ticks for about 20 seconds then immediately goes away. I've put 57k problem free miles on this car and never touched it.. just let it warm up 20-30 seconds and it's perfect. Really isn't a big deal ask any mechanic it's pretty common actually but you can get it all done for reasonable and have a perfect car. The car is pretty straight but has a few dings and scratches so I'm open to all offers! Thanks for looking. *onky selling because I bought a new truck*

Title: Volvo C30 T5 R-Design 6 Speed Manual-GREAT SHAPE! Hatch Back Red
Description:
For sale is my Volvo C30, T5, 6-speed manual, R-Design with Dual-Toned Leather. 

I have babied this car. I searched high and low for it years ago-it was not an easy car to find! Simply needing a rig with more space now. 

I worked for Volvo for a time and this car has received all its routine maintenance along with all major part changes on schedule (timing belt, etc). I had the dual-toned leather seats re-dyed a couple years ago. Had exterior all buffed out about a year ago. Regular detailing. I take very good care of this car, cosmetically and mechanically. I have had all-weather floor mats and trunk mats in this car the entire time I have had it.  

Semi-high miles because I used to have a job where I did a lot of freeway travel. The last couple years have solely used it as a short distance commuter. 

Handles great, truly sporty and such a fun car-I will miss it. Only serious buyers. Please keep in mind this is a rare car and Kelly Blue book does not take into account the availability of any given vehicle on the market.

Title: 2007 Toyota Tacoma V6 4DR Double Cab 4WD 362142 -_Ÿ_˜ -LOWEST RATES -
2003 Toyota Camry 4 cyl 5 speed manual
Description:
2003 Toyota Camry 4 cyl 5 speed manual

 You read that right, it's a mother freakin unicorn.  The time has come for me to part with what has been the best car I've ever owned...my 2003 Toyota Camry with a 4 cylinder and a 5 speed manual transmission.

 Does it have a rear view camera?  No.  But it has mirrors and windows and if you open your eyes and turn your head, you can see what's behind it.  I know right?  You might have to roll down the windows because the tint keeps the car cooler than its driver!

 What's the mileage you ask?  It's a Camry.  It doesn't frickin matter what the mileage is!  But if you really want to know, this one's got 224kish on the odometer and they are all PNW miles.  It's mind boggling how many freeways we have and this car has been on every single one of them.  It's seen some beautiful shit out there...and some not so beautiful, but let's not talk about those.  Moving on...

I have kept up with the maintenance as much as I needed to.  There's no timing belt, that's right, this beast has a timing chain.  Built to survive even the crappiest drivers and the zombie apocalypse.  It drinks about a quart of oil every 1000 miles or so but so far, there are no drips in my driveway.  She's a thirsty one, but hey, at least I put the oil in it.  I'm pretty sure the manual lists oil type as, "optional."

 This car also comes with the most effective anti theft system on the market today...a clutch.  When thieves are on the prowl they are intrigued by the awesomeness, but then when they see the pedal on the left, they keep on moving to the Honda Civic parked next to it.  They look, but don't touch.  But you?  You can touch all you want if you pay for it!  #ThatsWhatSheSaid

Does it have a clean and clear title?  Yes.  I purchased this BAMF from Beaverton Toyota and paid it off, $200 a month at a time.  It's all mine now; it can be yours for $2900.  If you need to negotiate price, thanks for reading but you're not worthy of owning this fine specimen.  Keep scrolling and find one with a rebuilt title.  No seriously, because they are probably cheaper than this one.  Or maybe look at a Corolla or a 1990 Accord instead?  Both fine vehicles, but this one's better and it's definitely tougher than a Nissan Altima.

 Look, this car screams, "I'm a practical adult, but still want driving to be fun!"  It's got 4 doors, 5 seat belts, and tons of visual sex appeal.  Except where the cover is missing on the bottom of the front bumper.  You can stick a fog light in there but I leave it empty to remind me just how bad ass this car is.  Yeah, it's missing the cover, but you should see the raccoon...the one I didn't see in the middle of the night running across the road in Eastern Oregon.  I only guess it was a raccoon because I could make a hat out of what was left of it.

Because you twisted my arm, and not because I already have another one, I'll even leave in the stereo system.  It's got an Alpine deck with blue tooth and I also upgraded the speakers.  Will it blow the clothes off your date?  No.  Will you get a ticket for talking on your cell phone while driving?  Also no.  Call it a wash?

Speaking of wash, I just got the car detailed.  Vacuumed and everything.  It's ready for you to do Camry things with it.  Get your groceries?  Okay.  Go on a road trip to Texas?  Sure, why the hell not?  Race a Ferrari?  Hell yes, this one has a clutch pedal, remember?  That shiny new red Italian horse shifts itself...what fun is that?

So why am I selling it?  Because I finally bought the 4runner I always wanted but never needed, thanks to the amazing versatility of the Camry.  Have I mentioned how big the trunk is?  Who's that driver with the junk in the trunk?  It's me!  It's you!  It's your friend who needs to buy a cheap ass car!

Oh yeah, and it's not Beige!  Now shoot me an email with your contact info and let's get this deal done...Your cash for this priceless piece of automotive history: my 2003 Toyota Camry.

Title: 2009 Dodge Grand Caravan SXT Stow-n-Go
Description:
I've listed it under what avg blue Pok is because it has one small thing wrong, which is easily fixable and I am planning on doing it this summer when I have time. The driver's side power door needs a new wiring harness. The power open works everytime but the power close only works every once in a while. There's slice where it bends and when it's fully extended, it doesn't make contact. Wrecking yard has one and should be an easy swap. 

Has awesome storage with the stow-n-go seating, either have the whole back open, and can lay a mattress down and sleep or carry all kinds of stuff, or put the seats up and have in-floor storage for snacks, toys, or bags that would normally be at your feet. 

As it is 10 years old, it's got some rock chips on the front as does most cars of this age. No real body damage, dents or large scratches, Clean title, kept up on regular maintenance, brakes are due to be done this summer, will do them sooner if someone pays asking price.  ERG valve replaced this winter, and it has a smart sensor that tells your phone average MPG, where you parked, Trip logging (time/date/miles traveled/gas used/estimated cost...etc), and what's wrong if the check engine light comes on. 

Serious interest/offers only, will delete when sold

Title: 2004 GMC 2500HD Sierra SLT pickup
Description:
We are selling a loaded and very well maintained GMC 4x4 crew cab truck with a 6.6 liter Duramax diesel engine and an Allison automatic transmission.

Overall this is a super comfortable, really clean, good pulling, and good looking pickup that has had regular, proactive maintenance.

This pick-up has power steering, locks, windows, seats and mirrors. The seats are leather and heated they also have a power lumbar support pillow.  The interior is in excellent condition and the air conditioning will make you cold on a hot day.  Cruise control.

Back windows are tinted.  Radio/CD player with 6 CD changer.  Front head-rests have small screens for viewing DVDs in the back seat.  Also has digital programming so you can track average or instantaneous fuel mileage and many other functions.  Has the GM Oil Life Monitor and will tell you when to change engine oil.  Doesn't leak or burn any oil.

Truck has hardly done any towing or hauling.  It was my Dad's before it was ours and he used it as his daily driver and put about 80000 miles on it as a commuter.  GVWR is 9200 lbs. The bed has a spray in liner and a flip up 2 5/16" gooseneck ball.  Comes with a rigid, folding bed cover. Also has a 16000 lb aftermarket receiver which was installed less than 3000 miles ago.  Comes with a Prodigy 2 electric brake controller to go with the stock tow package.

Wheels are brand new and tires are Michelins with less than 15000 miles on them. Spare tire is brand new.

Transmission was flushed about 4000 miles ago. Injectors were replaced about 20000 miles ago and the brakes are brand new with less than 100 miles on all new rotors and pads.  Alternator has less than 3000 miles on it.  We have receipts for all these maintenance items.  

We really like this pickup and would love to keep it, but we're trying to get started in farming and need to sell it to buy some farm equipment.

A few not so great things: The windshield has a crack which is just out of direct view for the driver.  One of the front head rests is a little messed up on the back side where the DVD screens were installed. The bed cover has some discoloration but it does keep out most of the rain.  One reflector is missing on the inside of one of the back doors.  

This is a really nice four door / quad cab / double cab with one of the best engine and transmission combinations ever put together in a diesel pick up.

Title: 1998 Jetta (Gasoline) - Mechanic Special
Description:
So this car was running on Wednesday when I took it to Freddie's, but then it didn't start after I bought my groceries. It was running reasonably well for a 20 year old car previously. I had it tuned up at Lucky's a few months ago and it was running well, getting me around town and up and down I-5 once or twice a week. 
But then it started and then it died. 

It was having some cranking sluggishness when starting earlier this week. The car turns on but doesn't crank now. Could be a bad battery, could be the alternator, could be the clutch not engaging, could be the starter, could be the battery cables. I don't have the time to figure that out, and I'm through with this car. The inside is a little beat up, but it's not moldy.

Again, this car isn't running; I'm really only interested in serious offers. 
Asking $600.00 -or- OBO.

I'm moving in a few weeks and the vehicle needs to be sold before that happens. 
So if you are a mechanic, or you are a VW enthusiast you might be able to do something with this car.

Title: 2002 Kia Rio, Only 41,000 miles
Description:
Hi, I'm an OSU student who is no longer in need of my car and realizes car insurance and student loans aren't a great combo. I got my 2002 Kia Rio at the beginning of this year and it has worked great for me. Some things to know: 

1. The car currently has 40,550 miles on it, which is incredibly low for a car from 2002 (A quick Google search says cars are driven on average 15,000 per year). The lady I bought it from had the car for 14 years and said she almost only drove it to work, which was apparently close to her house.

2. It's a stick shift. If you're a younger person like me, this likely means learning how to drive a manual. This would be a fairly good car to learn on since the clutch seems pretty forgiving, but don't really know how new manual cars compare since I haven't driven one and they aren't really made much anymore. If you have no clue or need a few pointers on how to drive a stick shift, I would be happy to help. 

3. If you look online for the mpg, google will tell you it gets 27-city and 32-highway, which has been accurate for this car in my experience, one time I got around 25 on the highway but I was going around 85 on I5 so that's pretty reasonable. 

4. I'm still using the car, and am thinking it would be helpful for moving out of my apartment, which I will be doing on the 15th of June. However, if you want to purchase the car before then, I can make it work, just give me some heads up so I can get it all cleaned up. 

5. All the windows and doors are manual. This can be a pain, but at least you don't need to worry about them breaking. 

6. I got new tags this year which cost a bit (112$ if I remember right) so you won't need to worry about that. (Lasts two years)

Title: 1989 GMC suburban 3/4 ton
Description:
I have a 1989 3/4 ton suburban for sale.  I have replaced the engine with a new GM 5.7 crate motor.  It has a new radiator, power steering pump and steering box, distributor, alternator, TBI, fuel sending unit.  It has 3:73 gears with the rear a full floater and I have the brackets and some other parts to put disc brakes on the rear.  I also have put new shocks and new steering stabilizers on it.  It has a 4" lift.  The interior is in good shape and it has the third row seat.  It has the barn style doors as you can see in the pictures.  The transmission is a TH400.
The headliner was sagging so I pulled it out and put the trim back in and it looks fine.  It will need new tires.  I have not charged the AC, but we live in Oregon so I  just opened the wing windows.  It's not perfect but it runs and drives great.  I have taken it to eastern OR a few times with no issues at all.
You can contact me at  
.  I'm not interested in trades.

Title: 1974 VW Beetle Bug Pirate Style!
Description:
1974 VW Bug, Pirate Land Ship's engine less than 100 mi! 

Only 2 minutes from 6th and G St

Awesome black & white VW Bug. Started rebuilding this Baja Bug, but too many projects invoke review of priorities & preferences. We're moving next year and can't take it with us and we'd also like to use the funds to take a vacation this fall. So I thought the project better suited to someone who could put the cosmetics in their own style. (I thought of mounting a giant treasure chest on the back, but again, the new owner will find their own taste.)

Could be a lot of fun for anyone, but especially so for someone who loves the pirate theme and there are plenty of them in Oregon! If you like/would like to attend Pirate festivals such as Sea Dog Nights, Port Royal Sanctuary, Tortuga, Annual Pirate Party at Depoe Bay, Pirate Festivals at Rockaway Beach or Tillamook Coast, and Pirates of the Pacific at Brookings, this is the perfect project for you! Gotta love the antenna flying the jolly roger! Personalized license plate even says AARRR !!!!!

No extreme low balling or asking to make payments as those emails will simply be deleted. Partial trades considered if you have a used Cushman truck or something similar. No OMMP trade offers please. Let me know what you have to offer by responding through CL email. Serious buyers only!

Title: '97 Honda Accord, runs good
Description:
1997 Honda Accord, priced cheap because it has lots of minor issues and I have no time to fix them. But this thing cranks right up every time and still rides smooth. Selling because we got a newer car and don't need three vehicles. This car is perfect for a college student. The broken stuff can easily be fixed or just lived with. It'll get you from A to B.

The good: 
Clutch, tires, tranny, engine runs great. Interior in great shape, no rips or tears. 

The bad:
Slow leak in radiator, needs fluid every 1000 miles or so. Dings all over, paint fading in places. 

The ugly: 
Driver side handle isn't functional on the inside, and the power window motor is shot, so the window is rigged closed and the door won't open from the inside. To get out, I pop open the back door and reach around and open the driver door from the outside, but my wife can't reach so when she drives it she has to climb out on the passenger side.

That's the worst issue as far as daily use. Window motors are under $50 online, but I don't have the time to mess with it, and that would be stretching my mechanical aptitude anyway.   

Text questions to SevenSevenZero, EightFourOne, FourFourThreeTwo

My lose is your gain!

Title: 1996 Ford Explorer Xlt! Price reduced
Description:
ive owned this good old ford for a couple years now, and its been a great car. as far as SUV's go this year of explorer is great around turns and windy roads, never got a tippy feeling from it. it has a clean title, and as well it has 268,xxx on the motor and chassis, and 130,xxx miles on the transmission. the transmission was replaced when it was at 160,000, with a transmission that had 25,000 miles on it. the transmission is CLEAN and you can feel it when you drive. no lag, no slip, always knows what gear it needs to be in. the motor is still going strong, and i have always kept the oil good. starts up great and the heater and a/c work, but the ac usually needs for you to drive around for it to start getting very cold. cruise control works, and the easy switch between 4wd low and 4wd auto and 2wd is operating smoothly. there is a small panel window taken out, i was quoted 75$ for the glass awhile back. also doesnt have a stereo installed, but i have a new bluetooth one right here and i might get around to installing it before it sells and if not will include it. Has the sun roof, which works without issue.

overall a trustworthy rig, that has never left me stranded and never made me wish i had another car. it has some miles on the motor, but has been taken care of. And the transmission is good, which is a big factor. will be a great car for whoever decides to come take a look! has a clean title and tags are good until july.

contact me at 541 nine 8 one 76 seven 3, text or call

Title: 1995 Dodge Ram 3500
Description:
The info I was given on this truck from the Chrysler Dodge corporate office in Detroit is as follows: This is a custom crew cab that Dodge contracted out to a private fabricator and then re-sold on the lots.   They Did not sell well Because  they were  $15,000 more than a Chevy or ford crew cab at that time.  I have been told that there was anywhere between 6 to 80 of these out there.   I have not been able to verify that.  I Believe the fabricator was Carl Green.  I have included a picture of what we believe is the truck during the customization phase. I am not saying that this is the truck but we believe that it very well could be. 

 Truck originally came with a V 10. When I bought it, it had the 215 P pump Cummins 12 valve engine with an automatic. We switched over to the six speed manual.  

96 12 valve with 215 p-pump

05 nv 5600 6 speed with 271 transfer case

22.5 Alcoa aluminum rims with space adapters with double coin tires

4" tough country lift with custom ladder bars

06 double caliper piston brakes in the front

2012 steering 

02 Dana 60 front end (rebuilt in 2016) and Dana 80rear  with 4:11 gears

99 electronics and dash with heated seats and 5 additional 12v power supplies

2012 front bumper with fog lights

Upgraded tow mirrors with defrost 

Isopro gauges: turbo, barometer, fuel  

Custom glass and door panels for rear doors

Custom upholstered inserts for front door panels

Upgraded alpine stereo with 6 speakers, Maybe 8

4" exhaust

Protech toolbox and headache rack

Panasonic DVD player (no sound through stereo.  Needs compatible headphones)

Arma coating bed liner

Custom truck bumper on rear

Needs: windshield wiper motor as it's blowing the fuses.  E Brake light is constantly on in the dash.  Occasionally if you get on it, the clutch slips.  New clutch when we changed over to the six speed in 2015. . However, we should  have gotten a more powerful clutch as there is more power than what the stock clutch can handle.  There are some cracks in the Dash but currently there is a cover over it. It is just a plastic molded cover. The truck is currently being used on and off for some work projects but for the most part it sits. 

I do not know of any rust. The paint is worn on the hood. It may be worn on top of the truck cab as well. The bed was replaced and the color is just a little bit different silver than the cab. The interior was switched over to a 99 interior rather than the older 95 style. Custom panels were made for the rear doors to closely match that of the front. Electric switches were put from a Durango of a similar year for the rear doors and the main control panel switch at the drivers door. There is a crack in one of the plastic dully fenders. We have two extra dully fenders from the original bed.

This is a project truck we've been working on for several years so it has a few things to do still. It has been used as a work truck and is no way in a show condition.

Title: 1984 Volkswagon Vanagon
Description:
Non-running Vanagon for sale.  Very nice body with no rust and straight except for a few bumps (see pictures).  Factory body seams are good, no rust.  Rear wheel wells original and not smashed.  Original paint.  The red paint is worn in front as shown and oxidized all over.  

Original 1.9 liter engine and 4 speed.  I've started the engine a couple of years ago and drove the van around but the engine has a valve or two sticking (my guess) and runs rough.  I would consider the engine a core for a rebuild.  New radiator installed by previous owner.

Glass is all there and not cracked but needs new window seals everywhere.  Interior is all there as well.  Good enough for a driver but needs refreshing with new carpet and seat covers.  Headliner is good.  Rear seat folds to make a bed platform in the back.

Spare tire and mount in the back of the van behind the seat.  Looks like everything is there to put it back under the front of the van, but I haven't tried so not sure.  Tires are old and crusty and 14".

Clean Oregon title in my name.  Needs to be towed or hauled away.

Title: 2016 Hyundai Elantra Value Edition 4DR Sedan Value Edition 4dr Sedan 6A (US) -
2012 BMW 335i M-Sport Alpine White black leather/aluminum interior
Description:
*** I am willing to transfer my current loan over plus you pay $2000 cash. I owe about $19,000 on the car and am half way through a 5 year loan. This is a great opportunity as you will have less interest and be able to pay off the car in 2.5 years. Otherwise, it's $21,500 - we will handle the transaction at a local bank.

Wife going back to school soon so need to pickup a cheap, economical car. This thing is incredible for the price. It's perhaps the most desirable configuration for the E92. Alpine white. Black Dakota leather interior with brushed aluminum trim. LED Halo lights. M-Sport package comes with badges, shadow trim and aero of the body, lowered from factory, sport tune and M-Sport suspension. It drives much better than a standard 3 series. Nice 19" wheels as well. I also have new max performance summer tires installed with only 6,000 miles on them! You'll find others that just don't add up like this, like that ugly wood trim, weird color or no M-sport package which makes a HUGE difference in the look and feel of the car. 0-60 in 4.6 -300HP/300tq stock.

Before the warranty expired I had the windshield molding replaced, service done and O2 sensor replaced by dealer. After that I replaced the water pump and thermostat with brand new OEM parts. I can get the receipts. Also recently replaced the Coolant expansion tank. All the little things that break on these cars I've replaced already and are basically brand new. Oil change was at reputable indie shop using BMW approved LL oil (Motul) -which I can also get receipt for. Last oil change about 2000 miles ago I did myself with a BMW oil kit (BMW OEM oil and filter)

New top of the line performance tires installed about 6k miles ago. They are Continental Extreme Contact Sport - a brand new tire they just released. They have 90%+ tread left on them. These are direct competitors to the Michelin PSS and their new tire. They grip for days. I don't think there's a better tire for this car.

There are some minor scrapes and such like with most used cars. Of note are a small line on driver side door about 1/4" long, very tiny. A couple black scuffs that can be buffed out, also very small. Some curb rash on the wheels (from original lessee) and scuffs on under part of front bumper. Nothing that can really be noticed unless looked for and very close up. Also rear middle seat headrest seam has torn from the heat last summer. It's not a big deal but is there nonetheless. I have been using 303 protector and Lexol on the interior since I got the car about 2 years ago. Also wash at home with Maguires gold car wash and wax with Maguires pure Carnauba wax. Overall the car is in great condition for the miles and age. However, it was in a minor accident before I purchased it. No airbags deployed. The title is still clean.

*Note that this is the N55 engine model. The 2011 and previous e92's used the N54 engine. The N55 is a great engine and is reliable compared to the N54. The N55 uses a single twin-scroll turbo while the N54 uses twin turbos that have been known to cause issues.The N55 is a very solid motor and is one of BMW's most reliable to date. It is wroth the premium IMO to get the newer N55 engine models. They have been used since 2011 and in many of BMW's performance cars. The M3 and M1 used the S55 (variant) engine. The N55 get's up to 15% better gas mileage, has better low torque response and throttle response and better reliability as compared to the N54. The N55 engine made the "Ward's" list of "top 10 best engines" from 2011-2013 All the info is on the web, just do a google search.
