Title: Volkswagen Jetta TDI 2003 Manual, Diesel
Description:
2003 Volkswagen Jetta TDI
I am the second owner, and purchased it from my neighbor after graduating high school to use during college. He was a mechanic commuting 1.5 hours/day, and put the first 195,000 on the car. He personally performed all preventative maintenance on the vehicle himself, including a belt replacement around 190,000. Now I'm looking for something a little bigger considering I will not be commuting anymore. 

-Clean title
-Manual transmission with which I've never had issues. Still shifts smoothly.
-222000 miles, almost all highway
-Last oil change at 220,000 miles
-Battery replaced last year
-Tires have good tread, and were purchased last year at around 210,000 miles. 
-Automatic door locks and windows
-Plain interior, with gray cloth seats/panels and black dash. Interior is in good condition, and was recently detailed. Neither owner smoked in or abused the car. 
-Most recently got 46 mpg on a trip to California, driving conservatively

This car is and will continue to be a wonderful commuter. In the three years I've owned it, I've only had to replace the battery and tires, while getting 43+ MPG the entire time. That being said, the check engine light has been on for the past year, coding for an EGR issue - luckily, the EGR has to do with the exhaust, and does not affect the engine's functionality in any way. 

Please, do not hesitate to call or text me at the number above.

Title: Help from a Mechanic  to put my timing belt back together
Description:
I am looking for a nice, certified 
Mechanic who would be so kind as to helpful me put the remaining parts nd pieces of my cars timing belt assembly and such back together, as well as help me figure out why its leaking oils, and running a little weird. I had a friend help me replace it and he did a real sloppy job.. he rushed putting it back together took short cuts and such.
The timing belt is on but the other tgree serpentine belts are hanging. It looks like it just needs the upper part of the timing cover put on, and a few random bolts and screws put in as well. Im also hoping we can look over his work and find any additional errrors he made as to prevent my car from addtional problems down then line. Id also like help deciding if the motor was damaged when the belt broke. I did have him check the compression and he said it was good, but I wasnt there so I dont know how much of that is valid. Ive only reciently, this last year, started to learn how to work on cars, but being a women, I tend to not have the strength needed for most of the mechanical work. Tough as it has been I refuse to give up I just need someone knowledgeable and kind enough to help me. Im currently in corvallis as is my car.. I could pay for the help, but not very much. 
If intetested please contact me via email given above.

Happy Wednesday everyone!

Cheers,

Title: 1986.5 Pontiac Grand Prix Aerocoupe 2+2
Description:
One of 1118 manufactured, X amount to be raced as a stock car back in the day. Pontiac had record of selling 211. This car sold for $18,500 in 86. It was a no option car, came fully loaded and only in silver. The car came stock with a 305 V8 and a 4 speed auto transmission. 

 It ran fine till the computer crashed. I then pulled the intake and smog off the car and ran an old school intake and 4 bbl. It ran great but the transmission now wasn't getting signal to shift properly. I pulled the original engine and transmission and have stored indoors. Plan was to install a 4 bolt 350 and TH 350 transmission from a 70's pu. (needs output shaft swapped to a short shaft). Or shorten and balance the shaft?  Or be unoriginal and do an LS1 swap. I am the third owner and have had it for 13 years.

 All original engine parts / transmission come with this car, as do the 4 bolt 350 and Th 350 if desired.

 Interior has seen better days carpet and back seat are missing, console broken, misc damage on door panels. 
 
 Back window leaks at the top right, creating a rust stain at back seat. I think someone did repair before i got it.
 
 Body is solid with no rust to my knowledge, huge doors so hinges need new pins. Trunk lid is fiberglass, nose is plastic. 
Car needs paint. 
 
 Two sets of wheels, original 15" rallys no tires and 88 Monty Carlo SS 15" aluminum alloys on the car.


 This car has American History, that is as rare as the car itself. Designed to be more aero and raced only one season by few including Richard Petty (The King). I cringe at selling this car so please be kind and don't waste my time. I would be more than happy to show my car and talk. Ryan

Title: 2004 Ford Expedition XLT NBX
Description:
Selling my 2004 Ford expedition. It has about 88000 original miles. 4x4, Tow package, skid plates, no tire pressure monitoring system, no traction control 5.4 l V8 (16 valve not the 24).  This has been adult driven and owned. Oil change every 3000 miles I just recently did the transfer case, transmission and rear end service as well as rear brakes. It has some door dings around the vehicle and a small tear on the seam of the seat which I can have fixed or you can fix it yourself. It has a double din CD player with Bluetooth I'm going to leave in the amplifier that's under the rear seat. It is an 8 passenger with 3 rows. Flow master exhaust system K&N air filter . Thule roof rack I have both sets of keys with remotes. $8500 or best offer. 
This is my personal vehicle, but since I am the business manager for an auto dealer I currently have it on consignment on their lot so financing is available to qualified buyers.

Description:

Previous owner was a smoker so there are a few cigarette burns, I have cleaned the car out but could still use a deeper cleaning. I am asking $600 OBO as I just need to get it gone. Runs and drives exactly how it should without any fluid leaks. Body could use some cleaning up, but there aren't any leaks in the hardtop or other seals.
The 4.0 HO swap was done by the previous owner who was an independent mechanic. 
Has 4WD in 4-Hi and 4-Lo

Asking $7500 OBO or trade. Shoot me an offer, least I can say is no.

Recent Service(within last 500 miles):

- Oil change

-Thermostat
-Thermostat housing gasket

Stuff:

Title: **Beautiful 2012 HYUNDAI AZERA-limited
Description:
Like New- Technology package, Excellent condition.. One of the reasons we bought this car is its spacious cabin that has enough room to comfortably seat four tall adults. There's also a ton of trunk space for a lot of luggage.Â  The exterior styling and interior design are much more dramatic and appealing than other sedans. It has an impressive number of features (leather seating and a navigation system are standard, for instance) and a more powerful, fuel-efficient V6 engine.  It gets 30+ mpg highway and 27 in town. 
Â 2012 Hyundai Azera is classified as a large sedan and is offered in a single, well-appointed trim level. Standard features include 19 inch wheels, automatic headlights, foglights, heated mirrors, leather upholstery, a 10-way adjustable driver seat, an eight-way adjustable front passenger seat, heated and air conditioned front seats, dual-zone automatic climate control, heated rear seats, a tilt-and-telescoping steering wheel, an auto-dimming rearview mirror, 60/40-split-folding rear seats, a navigation system, BlueLink telematics and a 10-speaker Infinity sound system with a CD player, an iPod/USB audio interface and HD radio.
This car has a Technology package, 19-inch wheels, a panoramic sunroof, xenon headlights, a power rear sunshade, manual side window sunshades, a power-adjustable steering wheel, driver seat memory functions, a driver seat cushion extension, ventilated front seats, rear parking sensors, interior ambient lighting and a premium Infinity 12-speaker sound system.
Standard safety features on the 2012 Hyundai Azera include antilock disc brakes, traction and stability control, front and rear side airbags, full-length side curtain airbags, a driver-side knee airbag and active front head restraints. Hyundai's BlueLink (which is similar to GM's OnStar service) also provides SOS assistance and automatic crash notification.  The Insurance Institute for Highway Safety awarded the Azera its highest score of "Good" for the car's performance in frontal-offset and side-impact crash tests.
All maintenance done at Certified Hyundai dealers and I have ALL service records. Female driver who babied this car. 82,000 easy miles. $1,100 under Kelly Blue Book. 
Asking $13,900. OBO.

Title: "The Beaver" - Orange 2014 Smart ForTwo (451) Pure Extras + Bike Rack
Description:
Our family has affectionately named this car "The Beaver".  It's an OSU Orange Smart ForTwo.  This little car is a blast to drive, and honestly, I want to keep it, but we don't need an extra car.  

While it is the "Pure" model it does have the heated seats and automatic windshield wipers, and manual mode for the transmission.

At only 22k miles this thing runs like new.  It was recently serviced at the Smart Center in Portland.

It has a really stout locking bike rack.  The bike rack is easy to remove (two bolts and it's off).

Anyways, as much as I hate to part with it, it's time.  Currently it's financed at SELCO so if you need to finance it, if you go with them it's a piece of cake as they can just copy all the info over from when we applied.  SELCO is pretty generous about loans as well. 

Give me a call or a txt come see the car and take it for a spin.  

Currently we're asking $8500 due to the low miles, but we will entertain other reasonable offers if we don't sell it soon.

Some quick facts.

It is gas, not electric.
It goes fast (Top speed is 100mph+)
Gas Mileage is about 35MPG in town or on the Highway.
It has a whopping 8 airbags and a steel roll cage, it is extremely safe. Here is the record from the IIHS for the Smart ForTwo - http://www.iihs.org/iihs/ratings/vehicle/v/smart/fortwo-2-door-hatchback/2014
It's bigger on the inside than the out (like a Tardis).  I'm 6' 4" and drive it to Portland regularly.
They are a blast to drive.

Title: 1974 FORD F-250 CAMPER'S SPECIAL - 7.6L GAS, LOW MILES
Description:
Though it saddens me, I am moving to Portland and have to part with my 1974 F-250. I purchased the truck three years ago and since then have made some major changes to it. For one, I had the brake system almost entirely redone with new lines in places, a new master cylinder, and new drums and discs. A completely custom 3 3/4" exhaust system installed by high performance racing in Southern California leading to exhaust tips the same size. The engine was also replaced 3 years ago, when I took the .390 out and put in a .460. Now with under 10k miles on it, it sits with an MSD distributor and ignition setup and almost every new part in between. I have documentation for all of the parts that have been added or replaced over the years, so I can provide as much proof as needed. The radiator, steering column, and spark plug were all replaced a month ago, and the truck is in great running condition. I often joke that the only things that aren't new on the car are the drive shaft, the tranny, and the driver himself. There is well over 10 thousand dollars in this truck and has been treated right. The truck runs and looks great aside from one minor blemish on the passenger side (which I included a picture of), and deserves to go to someone who will really care for it. 

Let me know if you have any more question, 

Text/Call preferred 

-Travis W Johnson

Title: 1997 Ford explorer XL 4x4
Description:

It also comes with 4 studded tires used a couple times by previous owner[NOT on rims, which is why I never used them] has clean title. Looking to get $1,800 [price is firm] Also comes with the back passenger break pads, I never got around to putting them on.  The other 3 sets are done though.

Title: Jeep Cherokee 96

We're finally selling our Jeep Cherokee. It has been a trusty vehicle but it's time for us to get something newer. It's perfect for off roads or in town commutes.

Alternator

Spark plugs and wires

Tires

Radiator 

Fuel filter

Air filter

Serpentine belt

Battery 

IAC valve 



        Brand new parts: 

Starter

Crankshaft positioning sensor

Both headlights

Brand new tags as of February 

        It also has a full size spare tire and a trailer hook up with the hitch

        Extra parts included(most brand new):

Full set windshield wipers

Distributer cap

Fully ceramic headlamp harnesses for front left and right

Brand new serpentine belt

Title: 69VW BEETLE-Restored
Description:
This is a 1969 VW bug that has undergone a complete body off restoration. The paint alone should win a best paint award at a car show and the rest of the car flows with the same perfection. Rebuilt trans, new axles, clutch, 1641cc engine with updated oil cooler and dual port heads, new carb, electronic dist., and so on. All new brakes with updated front disc. New floor pans and cables covered with sound insulation and new carpet. Inside has all new upholstery  with two tone seats and door panels, new headliner and all glass rubber. There is also a new dash plus a four gauge panel under the dash that includes volt, fuel, oil press, and a tach, all of which are VDO German gauges. New 8 spoke EMPI wheels with the spokes painted to match the car and new tires.
The car has been done for about six months and 300 miles ago and all is perfect and ready to drive anywhere that there is not a shopping cart. For more info and there is lots-give me a call or whatever. Thanks

Title: 2014 FORD F250 SUPER DUTY 4X4 DIESEL CREW CAB LARIAT (SHORT BED)
Description:
I have a 2014 Ford F250 4x4 Crew Cab Lariat (Short Bed - 156") Diesel Truck that is for sale.  This truck is in excellent condition and has been well taken care of.  It has had all of its scheduled maintenance done on time and by a Ford Dealership (Kendall Ford and Skyline Ford).  This truck is loaded with a quite a few extras items that have been added:

ARMA Coating in Bed
Leveling of the Truck
Air Bags for Bed of Truck
Wireless Compressor for Air Bags
Fifth Wheel Hitch Brackets (Made for a Short Bed Truck)
35" TOYO Tires
20x9 Raceline Assault Chrome Wheels
Total Extras = $6,354.00

This vehicle also has the following:
6.7L Power Stroke v-8 Diesel
Chrome Package
Chrome Angular Cab Steps
FX4 Off-Road Package
Skid Plates
Rapid Supplemental Heater
UpFitter Switches
Lariat Ultimate Package
Navigation System
Power Moon Roof
Remote Start (with 2 keys)
Tailgate Step
Heated/Cooled Front Seats
Heated Seats in Rear
Power Passenger and Driver Seats
Memory Driver Seat (for 2 drivers)
All Weather Mats
Dual Zone Climate Control
Hill Start Assist
Reverse Sensing and Rearview Camera
Trailer Brake Controller
Trailer Sway Controller
Trailer Tow Package

Again, I have taken exceptional care of this truck.  The only reason that we are selling is that we are in the process of purchasing a new 2018 Ford and I do not need two :-).  This truck is amazing, has everything you could ask for on a truck and looks amazing.  The only thing that is wrong with it is there are two pieces of molding on both sides that are losing their platinum tri-coat color and there is also a small scratch on the driver side bed (see picture).  It has never been in any type of accident (see car fax) and again is in excellent condition.  I have all of the maintenance records for every single thing that has been done on it since we bought it new.  Kelly Blue Book and Carfax have it listed at $44,570 but that amount does not include all of the added items that are listed above.  If you add that in along with the KBB and Carfax price, you get $50,9240.00.  

Give me a call, text, or email if you are interested.  $46,500.00 OBO.

Additionally, if you are looking for a truck that comes with the Fifth Wheel Hitch, the Hitch that I have for this truck is a "SuperGlide PullRite" Model 4400 that can pull up to 20,000 lbs.  Brand new purchase price is $1,400.00.  This hitch is designed for short bed trucks.  Most fifth wheel hitches require that you exit the vehicle and pull the lever when attempting to make a sharp turn with your trailer.  The allows the trailer to move back so you do not impact the rear of the truck.  The SuperGlide is an auto adjusted hitch that automatically moves when needed.  It is amazing and works exactly as described.  I would be willing to let it go with the truck for an additional $1,000.00.  Another great thing about this hitch is that once you are done pulling the trailer, you can easily remove the hitch and the brackets without any tools.  It comes right out, and posts come out and you have the bed of the truck back.

Title: 1999 Suburban 1/2 ton - 113K miles
Description:
We have a Suburban that we hardly ever drive, We purchased it around 6 years ago to use around the property and it only gets used a few times a year.

Asking 4500 OBO 

Willing to trade for decent Quads 

Here's the good
1999 Chevrolet Suburban
113K miles
350 V8 Gas Engine - AUTO
4x4
Power windows - all work
Power seats - work
Power mirrors - don't work
Cloth interior - no tears or bad wear on seats
Its in decent shape for a 1999 vehicle
Motor is strong and runs great
4x4 works but we never use it
Tires are almost new, maybe have 5K miles on them, we purchased them a few years ago but hardly drive the truck.

Here's the things that don't work
Gas Gage has never worked since we bought it, we re-set the mileage tracker to 0 every-time we fill it and run it to 350 - 375 miles and then fill it up and re-set the tracker and have never had any problems

The AC needs re-charged - we hardly drove it so we did'nt really need the AC
Heater blows great but the fan only seems to work on High 

Interior is in decent shape for as old as it is, no tears or heavy wear on any of the seats, the rear portion was used to haul things in it so the carpet is a little dirty and worn.

The front side speakers have some rust on the factory grill

Other than that, the vehicle has always turned right over and ran great the entire time we've owned it. 

Text or call with any questions
John

Title: The Price is Right
Description:
COME ON DOWN!... and pick up your new car!

Pros;
1) It starts and runs.
2) Aftermarket CD player with 12" woofer in the trunk (8 gauge wiring so you can go bigger), JBL speakers in the back deck.
3) 3 ignition keys and 3 door(no chip) keys
4) Good MPG (25+)
5) Siped Les Schwab tires with ~ 50%tread on them
6) Clutch replaced 1.5 years ago
7) Low financial barrier to own Ã°

Cons;
1) Check engine light on
A) Code P0016 displays on the dash(P0016 - Crankshaft Position - Camshaft Position Correlation (Bank 1 Sensor A)) (cam shaft
position sensor and crank shaft position sensor have been replaced, that turned the light off for approximately two months)
a) https://www.obd-codes.com/p0016
2)Oil light comes on after driving for a short while (I haven't been able to figure this one out, it doesn't overheat)
3) Minor body damage / minor interior trim damage
4) Turn signal works intermittently
5) Engine sound (knocking noise)
6) CD's don't always eject properly
7) Dogs were often in this car (dog hair carwash vacuum wouldn't remove, water spots on front passenger seat)
8) Unseated spark plug barrel in two middle cylinders (they rise up occasionally and a little oil is lost due to this)

I have been using this car to commute to and from work for five years. It has been a reliable car. I'm selling it because I recently purchased a newer model. Would be a great car for someone making short trips (student, local) or you could turn it into a mobile sound system for tailgating. Please read whole list and feel free to ask questions. $750 OBO.

I'm down for the idea of trades, but cash is preferred. All offers will be considered. Please don't waste your or my time, only contact me if you're a serious buyer, and if you're a scammer, there's a special level in hell for you.

Title: Saab 9-3 Convertible 2003
Description:
Offering my beautiful 2003 Saab Convertible for sale. For you "Saab people", you understand the Saab driving experience and this Pearl White car is in excellent condition and is truly an eye-catching machine.  Saab is well known for its incredible handling which is unbelievable, and the turbo delivers power instantly when it is asked for. It corners like a dream, climbs hills with ease and passes with plenty of power; all while getting 27-35 mpg.  As I said, the paint is Pearl White and is in beautiful condition. Interior is a 9 out of 10. Leather seats and interior, carpets etc show very little wear. The climate control system is perfect...Air conditioning system was completely replaced last September and blows cold and the heater blows hot.  Power windows, power seats, mirrors all work perfectly. Tires are in excellent condition. Cruise control, heated seats, traction control all perfect condition.  AM/FM/CD sound is original equipment. Electric controls for the top work as they should. Back window is clear. Car has no mechanical problems whatsoever. 5 speed manual transmission gives the driver complete control over the vehicle, shifts perfectly. Instruments all function properly. Turbo functions fantastically and does not smoke even a tiny bit. Has very low miles and should easily be good for another 150,000 or more. Includes car cover and wind screen (which reduces the air blowing things around when the convertible top is down. It is visible in one of the photos).

I am selling this car because first of all I have too many cars and secondly I do not drive this one enough (have garaged it during the winter months). I will eventually be looking for the slightly larger 9-5 sedan to replace this car. I have owned several Saab's, including a 1989 900 convertible, a '95 9000 (which I sold after it reached 300,000 miles) and a 2002 9-5. This is truly a beautiful car, the nicest Saab I have owned. 

Consider this Saab, which is similar to BMW, Mercedes in style and handling, but costs thousands less. Call or text. Include my name (Steve) in your text so I know you are not a robot.

Title: 2006 Pontiac Grand Prix... Alotta Car for the Money
Description:
Nice clean, comfortable family or starter car always serviced locally and well cared for by a couple old folks like us.

The car isn't perfect, the CD player doesn't work, but the monsoon speakers and radio do... It has a little curb rash on one wheel, and a few scratches... but if it was perfect I wouldn't be selling it... or if I was it would cost a lot more.  

The car has never let us down, has recent brakes, tires, spark plugs and wires, the cooling system was flushed and serviced this last winter and we've had it serviced regularly here at Point S / Canaga Tire in Lebanon.  AC blows cold... starts every time... gets good gas mileage if you stay out of the SuperCharger, and it's taken us on many adventures.

Now though... We've become old folks with a new Buick, and the GP needs a good home.  I'll listen to realistic offers, but I don't HAVE to sell the car and am not interested in somebody coming to look at it and picking it apart.  IT has flaws... it's not new.

Email, Call (54-one Four-09-Three-Four-5-Two) or Text to arrange to see or drive...or with any questions.  I work during the day and will respond when I can.

Title: Chrysler Pacifica -low miles, clean comfy cruiser/commuter, great deal
Description:
I'm selling this Chrysler Pacifica for well below the KBB value because I'm moving by the end of this week and need to sell it before then. It's valued closer to $4,250 but I'm asking $3,250 or best offer.

This car has only had one pair of owners, my parents, and I'm selling it for my pops. It's in great condition both in and out and my mom only used it to putt around town. 

I just recently had a pre-trip road check by Les Schwab and everything is in good shape with tires and suspension, oil was just changed last week and it's up-to-date on almost all scheduled maintenance. It could use some new transmission fluid, ~$150, which is another reason for discounting the price.  

Power windows, seats, leather, and sunroof are all in good condition. Seats fold down nicely and can fit 7. There is a small dent in the right front fender, and there are some scratches here and there on the sides. Also has working trailer plug-ins and hitches for towing.

Title: 1984 Crew Cab Chevy 4x4 383 Stroker
Description:
This is a truck my uncle had for many years (1992) before selling to me last year.    Unfortunately, we just don't use it and it has basically sat for the last 5 years with little use.   I've been wanting to use the motor in something else but that something else hasn't come along so I'm selling the whole business. The truck sends me straight from 6 to midnight every time I drive it, but I need to finish school more than I need the truck.  The truck is already experiencing some age issues which I've listed below.     It has a new Optima battery and fires right up and runs smooth.     The steering is nice and tight and goes down the road well.       Tags are good through 2018.   

BODY & CHASSIS: ---Factory 4x4 4speed -- it's not a hacked together jacked up truck
 -     1-ton  ( K30 )  3+3 cab
 -     4-wheel drive 4x4 works.   Heavy duty manual locking hubs. 
 -     4-speed manual transmission
 -     Forged aluminum wheels
 -     10 ply Toyo M-55 all terrain tires 20-30% tread  ($1,200 new)
 -     Positrack rear end with 3.73 gear ratio
 -     Bedliner
 -     Aluminum diamond plate toolbox
 -     Hella H4 & H1 headlights with 100 watt bulbs & separate wiring.    These are expensive lights and light up the road.       Two aircraft landing lights are mounted on bumper and are relayed off high beams.   Road signs will blind you.
 -     Rear backup lights on separate switch
 -     Hella air horns
 -     Rear brakes rebuilt with new brake shoes, wheel cylinders, axle seals. Fresh oil as well

ENGINE:
 -     383 cu-in small block stroker  (350 bored 0.030 over with 400 crank)
 -     Engine balanced, very smooth
 -     Forged pistons 10.2:1
 -     Dart-II heads with the big 2.02" valves
 -     Hooker Headers
 -     Edelbrock intake
 -     Edelbrock carburetor with electric choke
 -     Clutch and flywheel have less than 10k miles on them.
 -     Newish Optima battery
 -     Dual 2.5" exhaust with Magna flow mufflers.    VERY nice exhaust note, no exhaust leaks.
 -     Big radiator from a diesel pickup.
 -     New starter

INTERIOR:
 -     Pioneer stereo with 4 sets of speakers front rear + subwoofer (not currently wired because I took the amp)
 -     Seats & headliner reupholstered about 10 years ago.    Driver's side seat is starting to fray
 -     CB radio with magnetic antenna. Very fun on I5
 -     Carpet dirty.   Was replaced in about 2008, so it should clean up well.   It isn't very worn. 
 -     Nice high-end floor mats in front.

ISSUES:
 -     Window felt and door seals are old and should be replaced.   It has a fair amount of wind noise going down the road.
 -     Some rust forming in rocker panels by door.   
 -     It is generally a noisy truck.
 -     Interior kinda dirty.   Sorry, I'm not vacuuming.
 -     some rust forming on top of cab.
 -     speedometer needle bounces around some - have replacement speedometer assembly
 -     master cylinder seems to have a slight leak
 -     paint is pretty scuffed on the bed rails but is an easy fix

PRICE:  $7,500  .

Title: 1990 Cadillac Brougham D'Elegance.  Cruise in comfort and style!
Description:
Have you found your life to be lacking in panache?  If you had to Google "panache" then the answer is yes.  
Maybe you are tired of being shoehorned into an econobox with barely room for a friend and barely enough trunk space for a box of Kleenex?

The Cadillac Brougham is the pinnacle of automobile excellence. It floats down the highway and coddles it's occupants in the warm embrace of leather. This car was produced during a time when Cadillac was proud of their product; adorning practically every surface with it's crest...from the ignition key to the door lights. These cars retailed at over $40,000 in 1990!

This Caddy has been my parents pride and joy for decades and has been diligently maintained. Don't be afraid of the mileage because we've maintained it in tip top running and driving condition. The paint is showing some wear and the front seats have tears but this car still catches eyes wherever it goes. Be prepared to be stopped on the street by admirers and find notes under your windshield asking if you want to sell.

I've included many photos and tried to highlight the worst area of the car so there's no disappointments. We would love to keep this gem but it's now time to downsize. I'd have no hesitation in firing up this Caddy and driving to Vegas right now. Fuel mileage is surprisingly good, averaging about 18mpg.


1990 Cadillac Fleetwood Brougham D'Elegance
211,000 miles
5.7L fuel injected V8...burns no oil
Overdrive transmission 
Cruise control
Power windows
Power seats
Air conditioning blows cold and is converted to R134a
Power trunk lid
Power door locks and keyless entry
Rear view camera only (comes with original stereo which will plug right in)
Rear auto levelling air suspension
All maintenance is current

Recent repairs include:
-New water pump this month
-GM AC Delco remanufactured transmission in 2016 at 206k miles 3yr/100k warranty installed by Kendall Cadillac
-New Toyo tires in 2016 with alignment, very few miles on them
-New exhaust system 2016
-Interstate battery 2016
-All steering components and shocks replaced including steering gear box
-Windshield replaced
-A/C compressor replaced in 2015 and converted to R134A. New receiver dryer also.

The great:
-Car is incredibly reliable
-Very powerful and a joy to drive
-All the accessories work from the a/c to the opera lights and power trunk
-Body is very straight, rear fender filler panels aren't broken
-Incredibly well maintained including tune-ups, differential and bearing services and fluid flushes.
-Comes with some extra parts and service manuals

The not so great:
-Car has not been garaged and paint is chipping in several areas, small dings here and there. Top is faded but in good condition.
-One of the oil cooler lines has started dripping oil...common GM problem and the parts aren't expensive or hard to change
-Dash pad has a crack
-Driver door arm rest vinyl cracked
-Driver/passenger seats have torn leather.
-Chrome is in excellent condition but one of the tail light housings has rust starting
-Occasionally has a squeak in the steering wheel/column area
-Lots of wind noise. Window weather strip is old and brittle and need replaced. Door and trunk weatherstrip has been replaced.


Price is $3,500, sorry not interested in trades. If this ad is still up then it's available. Please email.






caddy, cadillac, fleetwood, deville, luxury, cruiser, brougham

Title: 1998 Honda Civic LX - 143,000 Miles
Description:
Welcome to my 1998 Honda Civic! I have had this car for a little over a year now and it has served me well. I'm moving into a new car so my civic has to go. Let me show you all the good stuff.

This is about as basic as you can get. Small 4 cylinder Automatic Four Door Sedan. It's a 1998 that only has 143,000 miles on it! It's got a LOT of life ahead. It's easy to drive and get terrific gas mileage (for a gas car) at 25 MPG in city and 33 MPG Highway. It's got Power Windows, Cruise Control, and AC! Great Starter Car or Cheap Daily Driver. 

I'm a non-smoker and have no pets. Clean title. Minor body damage (a few scrapes and paint). I have kept very good record of maintenance while I've had the car and if you contact me, I would be happy to share my maintenance record and car fax with you via email. The car runs well as long as you keep up on the oil. I'm also throwing in the floor mats, the club, rubberized trunk liner, and the sun shade.

When I bought this, I put in quite a bit of work regular maintenance wise. As a result, it has a lot of new consumables. All of the old parts were replaced due to age and condition.

List of new Components
**********************************************************
New Seat Covers - June 2017

New Cargo Mat - June 2017

New Front Brakes and Calipers - July 2017

New Tires - July 2017

Alignment with new Tire Rod - July 2017

New Battery - August 2017

New Spark Plugs and Wires - April 2018

New Distributor - April 2018

New Wipers - May 2018

AT Fluid - June 2018

**********************************************************

Like I said a lot of new consumables but there are a few things that the car needs done relatively soon. The Belts were recommended to be changed at some point but they work fine right now.

On June 2nd, 2018 I discovered a small crack in the windshield. Looks like a stress crack to me but it's an old car and the windshield is probably original. There's no leak that I see so it doesn't need to be replaced but if you want to replace it, I found a quote for $227 online.

The interior needed some work cleaning it when I got it and I brought it up to my daily drive standards, that being said, there are some cosmetic rips on the passenger side and a small crack in the rear bumper. The title is clean and a Car Fax shows the car has been in no reported accidents or damage. 

All that being said, I am willing to Negotiate starting at $2,400. I'm happy to answer questions about the car and send a maintenance record as well as a Car Fax.

Not looking to Trade, Cash Only. $2,400 OBO

Title: Running Camaro  Project-1978

Title: 2011 Jeep Wrangler Unlimited 70th Anniversary 4DR 4X4 4x4 70th Anniversary 4dr S
1G DSM project TALON TSi partout or whole plus extras
Description:
I have been storing it in hopes of finding the time to fix it but that looks unlikely now. I'll skip to the details

---link to a few more pics at bottom of ad---

BODY

CLEAN rust free STRAIGHT 1990 Eagle Talon TSi
manual trans works great no issues
3-bold LSD rear
one previous owner, older gentleman daily drove it since new
284k miles. Tons of service records. meticulously maintained
only downside to body is standard clearcoat issue 
MINT gray leather interior, no rips, tears, stains, etc.
MINT OEM floor mats 
OEM sunroof interior cover
OEM clip-in sunroof visor (RARE!)
OEM bag for sunroof to be stored in
OEM rear cargo cover
OEM manuals, dealer brochures, warranty cards, etc. 
OEM tool kit
OEM Radio and CD player that actually works
Air Conditioning still worked great when it was parked in storage
Factory service manual (printed from internet, in 3-ring binder)

ENGINE

When I got it the head gasket was bad. Parts installed are as follows
New radiator
Machined and pressure tested head, deburred and modified for better oil flow to and from the head
ARP head studs
4-layer Metal head gasket
Revised "3G" lifters (less ticking noise while running)
OEM water pump
GATES timing belt
OEM Balance Shaft belt
OEM tensioner
new injector seals
2g Exhaust manifold
New ebay 16g never been above stock boost level (284k on a 14b= lots of cracks in exhaust)
Ported 2g o2 housing
3" Turbo-back to nice muffler
ECU is stock 

Needs:
Wheels and Tires; currently on jack stands inside my shop
Battery (old one is probably dead, probably) 

THE BAD
I spun a rod bearing shortly after getting it running. So mad you cannot imagine. The oil pressure warning light never came on it just started knocking and seized. took about 3 city blocks from WTF is that sound to HOLY F- NOOO. Anyway, I bought a junkyard 6-bolt to rebuild, tore it apart to find that everything looked great inside despite having sat for a number of years before Pick a Part got it. I pulled the ECU from the parts car and it was filled with silicone where the caps leak so I suspect that was the issue the previous owner was fighting when it got parked. since then its sat inside with the car and it no longer turns. 

-to summarize, it comes with an entire 6-bolt, tore down to a short-block, and all the parts in totes (plus many extra). 

EXTRA PARTS
Motor I just mentioned
Front Mount intercooler made for a 1G with fogs (They work, I kept them)
255 Fuel Pump
evo 560cc injectors
2G MAF with hard intake pipe and cone filter
3-guage radio bezel for a single-DIN head unit
Glowshift Boost/oil pressure/air-fuel guages
extra ECUs, coils, cams, LOTS of little parts from my years of Mitsu hoarding.
broken passenger outer handle, its a DSM thing...
I was collecting parts for a well-rounded, reliable, comfortable daily with slightly more power than stock.  

Selling makes me sad. 

Considering offers

Title: 2006 Lexus GX470 w/new timing belt and water pump - 132k miles
Description:

There are no tears in the seats, but there is a loose stitch on the passenger door panel. It's only a minor flaw, though. It is also a non-smoker car. 

The car is mechanically sound. The car runs great, and I'm going to be sad driving anything else. It will need an oil change in about 1000 miles. The recent service was performed by a master Toyota technician that replaced the timing belt, water pump, hydraulic tensioner, serpentine belt, and radiator(with new coolant) within the past 1000 miles.

Title: 2007 Nissan Xterra ONLY 104k miles! Excellent condition
Description:
2007 nissan xterra 
condition: excellent 
cylinders: 6 cylinders 
drive: rwd 
fuel: gas 
odometer: 104000 
paint color: grey 
size: mid-size 
title status: clean 
transmission: manual 
type: SUV 
I love this vehicle, but it's just a little bit more than I need. It is in perfect working condition, with only 104k miles! 6-speed manual transmission, AC, tilt, cruise control, PW, PDL, upgraded alloy wheels, BF Goodrich all terrain tires (with 75% tread!), pioneer receiver deck with cd, MP3, and Bluetooth, for hands-free calling. It also has a trailer hitch and a fresh oil change and air filter. 
This vehicle is beautiful and in immaculate condition. 
I'm looking to get out from under the payments and into something a little smaller. The ONLY issue this vehicle has, is that the driver side door has a tired window regulator which makes the window sluggish sometimes.
Also, contrary to popular belief, Nissan did make 2WD Xterra's... This is a REAR WHEEL DRIVE Xterra, not a 4x4. This is the second Xterra I've owned, the first was a 4x4, and I actually only ended up using the 4WD only once in four years. These short, wide wheel bases do very well in snow and offroad, and get better mileage than their 4x4 counterparts.
The 4.0L V6 gets about 18 to 20 miles to the gallon, and is definitely no slouch on the highway. It'll put you back in your seat! 
There is one tiny spot on the driver side seat where the fabric is becoming a little bit thread bare... But it's hardly noticeable. 
Asking $6850 obo, no lowball offers and serious inquiries only please. 
If interested, please email or text me. Thanks for looking. _Ÿ™‚

Title: 2003 GMC Sierra 2500HD 4X4 ECSB
Description:
212xxx miles

6.0 Vortec, ECU has been tuned with EFI live to delete torque management, rear O2, and speed limiter. I can turn it back to factory if you need to pass emissions.

Automatic 4L80E
New venture 263 push button transfer case
Gabriel shocks, stock height suspension
Rear full floater 14 bolt with Detroit locker. A REAL Detroit, not some limited slip. Required swapping out the carrier from gov loc to open so the locker could be installed.

Driver seat bottom is less than a year old. New springs, foam, and vinal cover. Interior is great.
DuHa under seat storage box under the rear seats (not pictured yet)
Professional spray in bed liner

Fifth wheel rails installed
Class 3 tow package (factory)
Full size 285/75/16 Toyo MT spare in factory location
Dynatech split flow mufflers installed
Powder coated satin black, 8 wide American made wheels
65% Falken Wildpeak AT3/W tires (AMAZING traction) 
Some relatively new front end components, pitman arm, idler arm, passenger wheel bearing and CV axle, one upper ball joint, one tie rod.

It has rock chips in the paint from gravel roads, it has dents in the bed from the previous owner. It has scratches from using it as a truck and hauling stuff, some mountain pinstripes from driving past bushes while in the woods. 

A/C currently does not work. It's being worked on in spare time
Clock spring in steering column needs replaced. The driver airbag and steering wheel buttons don't work because of this. 


Was my daily driver/tow rig for small local things (cars, firewood, building materials, small boat)
I bought a new diesel, and don't need this truck anymore.
Reasonable offers entertained. Trades considered, but I need 3000 in cash at a minimum with trade.
Clean title in my name.
Only contact me to BUY the truck. Scammers and solicitors will be tormented verbally... A lot

Title: 2001 Pontiac Grand Am
Description:
2001 Pontiac Grand Am $850

Truthfully, this has been a fantastic car. I've had it for twelve years, and it's only needed to go to the shop twice. It hasn't broken down for 4-5 years, and has only needed flat tires fixed. Battery has died once or twice but that's probably my fault.  Runs great. I make ~60 mile round trip to Corvallis and back 3-4 times per week. Body is in great shape. Interior is in good shape. Some rust stains in trunk. Roughly 25-30 MPG. Forest Green, 187,000 miles,

Comes with free doughnut (spare tire) and a rusty jack and tire iron!

Known problems:  The only real faults are the window motors are broken, meaning they can't be rolled up and down. Neither of the back 2 work, but they'll stay up. The shotgun one is stuck down, which sucks. Driver one works intermittently.
2 semi-large cracks are on the windshield, but do not impede vision.
Right sideview mirror is taped on.
AC works only sometimes.
One of the tiny fog lights is out. You don't need it anyways. Back left blinker is out.
One hubcap is cracked.
Sideview mirror controls are missing.
Needs an oil change.
 Otherwise tip-top.

If you have any questions or want to take this beast out for a test-drive, please email me.
Serious inquiries only, please. Slight wiggle room on price.

Title: 2011 Think City 2 seat All Electric Vehicle EV (similar to a Nissan Le
Description:
It is with mixed feelings that I am offering my 2011 Think City All electric vehicle up for sale.  It has been a great little car and is very fun to drive.  If you want an Exotic Vehicle (EV), there are less than 400 Think City cars that were sold in the United States.   Good comfortable firm seats and plenty of space for grocery's or even your large dog in the rear hatch area.  I saved so much money on this car over the last 5 years, I was able to upgraded to a newer EV.  This is a great little city car that is fun to drive and easy to park.  It is 6 inches wider and 2 feet longer than a Smart for two, (which people often mistake it for), but this is much smarter and in my opinion a much better car.  It is a solid little car that has 27 cubic feet of cargo space behind the two front seats.  I have achieved up to 80 miles on a single charge and live in mountains where my elevation for a round trip to town drops 2,000 feet and then back up.  With instant torque off the line it will pull away from many other economy cars and handles quite well with the low center of gravity.  With fairly aggressive driving and AC running cold, I have no problem reaching 60+ miles per charge in moderate weather.  It does quite well in the snow and I have a extra set of steel rims that may be available with Michelin X-Ice snow tires if you are interested or live in a snow area.  I think it will only take cable chains, but with the X-Ice tires I have never had to put the chains on, even in 6" of snow on the road, I just plowed though it.  

I usually get about 3 miles / kWh so the cost to drive 3 miles will be the cost of 1 kWh of electricity.  It adds about 250kWh / month to the electric bill when I drive about 750 miles each month.

It has new summer tires with only a few thousand miles on them and very good tread left.  It includes a 120V charger (level 1) which works well but takes 2-3x longer than a level 2 charger (240V).  I charged with a level 1 for several months until I installed a level 2 EVSE.  The cars onboard charger is a 3.3kWh, so at a completely drained battery it will charge in about 8 hours.

This car has driver and passenger side airbags, daytime running lamps.

This car has been upgraded with the following:  New front 5-1/4" speakers, added rear speakers, rear tinted windows and tinted rear hatch window, daytime running lamps,  External PCU charger fuse-holders, Automatic delay on ac / heater on startup.  Trans-axle has had the 25,000 mile oil change and that is about all that is required for maintenance other than wiper fluid and tire rotation.

This car is located in in northern California.  The reason I am posting this in the Portland area is because I believe if this car is sold out of the state of California, your local state rebate for all electric vehicles may still be applied to this car.  Also Portland has a Think Service center and about 60-70 other Think's locally.  (for example: There is a $2500 rebate in Oregon and their website states if the vehicle has not been registered in the state, it is eligible for the rebate.  Disclaimer:  It is your responsibility to confirm it will be eligible in your state for any rebate.  Rebate has been claimed for California sale and car is registered in California through 2019)  There may also be utility rebates for electric vehicles.  For example, PG&E offers a $500 rebate and all you need is your registration address to match your PG&E billing address.
